models.description:
Service Usage

In CR4 the service usage scenario will allow Central Health to be the user issuing service a request via Websphere Process Server to CMAL for performing one of the above mentioned functions. As per the request CMAL will provide an asynchronous acknowledgement response and any further related notifications if requested.
models.readme:
Service Usage

In CR4 the service usage scenario will allow Central Health to be the user issuing service a request via Websphere Process Server to CMAL for performing one of the above mentioned functions. As per the request CMAL will provide an asynchronous acknowledgement response and any further related notifications if requested.

Service Behaviour

This service follows an asynchronous request and response pattern. Its asynchronous response may contain multiple responses. The service response is not tied to any time outs. This service responds with error conditions as specified in section 4 Return Codes and Messages.

Service Flow

A user system invokes Register Proposed Modified Person Alert service on the provider system;
Provider system receives the request and asynchronously responds with Register Proposed Modified Person Alert Response with a PAL Proposal Id.
If the request has Require Notification Of Progress set to TRUE the provider system will send notifications to notify any lifecycle change until the proposal is APPROVED, REJECTED or WITHDRAWN.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.

  1. In case provider encounters an exception scenario an asynchronous warning message will be sent as per section 4 Return Codes and Messages

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required

models.description:
Service Usage

This service will be engaged by GVP within the visa application process to retrieve the MAL status enquiry.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service will be engaged by GVP within the visa application process to retrieve the MAL status enquiry.

Service Behaviour

This service interacts directly with the CMAL System to retrieve the MAL status enquiry from the CMAL system for a given party Identifier and Identifier type. The service response includes the CMAL status details including MAL status flag. The service is a pseudo synchronous service. In the event the supplied Identifier cannot be resolved to CMAL recognised Identifier type an exception is returned. An exception is also returned of CMAL could not find the Mal status retain for the supplied Identifier.

Service Composition

The Services receives the PartyIdentifiers or PartyRoleIdentifiers which ever choice group information is supplied and retrieves the MAL status details from CMAL. The MALstatus can be retrieved within a given EnquiryContext if the consumer prefers to retrieve in which case the context details are also supplied to CMAL for retrieving.

Service Flow

A service request is initiated when a request for RetrieveMovementAlertStatus is received for a requested PartyIdentifier and Type or alternatives for a a CMAL recognised PartyRoleIdentifier and PartyRoleIdentifier Type.
The Service Validates the Consumer message and once the message is valid transforms the message to CMAL specific message format.
CMAL responds back with the MALStatus details including the MALStatusCode and relevant Alerts if applicable. In the event of a CMAL error the CMAL error is mapped onto the enterprise exception and returned back to the consumer. (Ref Alternate Flow AF1). Also in the event CMAL was unable to provide the response within the specified time frame a timeout message is generated and the consumer receives a time out exception response. (Ref Alternate Flow AF2).
The Service Validates the CMAL response and transforms the CMAL response into the service response
The Service Response message is returned back to the consumer as directed by the consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when CMAL is unable to successfully respond to the MALStatus Enquiry and returns back an error message. The errors reported can be of the nature of system errors, validation errors, processing errors or data unavailability errors (Ref Section 4 Return Code ALRT00003 to ALRT00006). The Error response is mapped to an enterprise exception message and returned back to the consumer. Thus SV367 service completes with an exception response to the consumer.
Sv367 makes a successful call to CMAL for a given party/Partyrole Identifier.
CMAL response RetrieveMALStatusResponse was an exception response.
CMAL exception is transformed to the SV367 exception response and returned back to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return SV367.MSG-E02 to the consumer.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

The service is used to request an external organsiation to conduct a criminal history police check on a person
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service is used to request an external organsiation to conduct a criminal history police check on a person

Service Behaviour

The consumer makes a NPHC SV399 request and receives a synchronous acknowledgement ; the consumer will then need to make a different call (SV400) to retrieve the NPHC result X number of minutes after the acknowledgement. The provider does not call back and provide results or errors.

Service Flow

A consumer will send a SV399 reques to the ESB which will transform into a NPCS CheckSubmitRequest message. The CheckSubmitRequest message is sent to NPCS visa the WSGW. NPCS will return an acknowledgement response which is also transformed into a standard DIBP acknowledgement.

Transformation

The SV399 request message is transformed using SV399_RegisterCriminalHistoryCheckRequest.xsl into a NPCS CheckSubmitRequest message

models.description:
Service Usage

This service will send off a request to an external organisation called National Police Checking Service (NPCS) to get a person's criminal history.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service will send off a request to an external organisation called National Police Checking Service (NPCS) to get a person's criminal history.

Service Behaviour

The consumer of this service will pass in a number of search criterias based upon this services mandatory required fields, the request is then transformed into a NPCS xml format called GetCheckResultRequest before being sent.

Service Flow

Consumer sends the request to ESB which will transform into a NPCS GetCheckResultRequest message. The GetCheckResultRequest message is sent to NSS via the WSGW. NSS may respond with a matched check for the person or error from the CheckSubmitRequest request or Check not yet complete

Transformation

XSLT RetrieveCriminalHistoryCheckStatusRequest is used to tranformed into GetCheckResultRequest

Service Usage

This service is used to match an applicant against risk profiles and models contained within various risk systems. The response will provide treatment advice to the VPO or CPO on what further action is required for this visa or citizenship application.

Service Behaviour

The consumer provides CVOR with information about the visa or citizenship application, and other historical information known to the department. CVOR makes subsequent service calls to Safeguards, RSS and GOIS systems and then consolidates the responses from these systems into the SV415 response message.

Note: As at the time of writing (28/09/2017) schema validation is turned off for the incoming request messages.

Service Composition

Transformation

The SV415 message is transformed within the CVOR java code into a SV081 provider message which is consumed by Safeguards.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service is used to perform Entity Matching of a particular person of interest.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to perform Entity Matching of a particular person of interest.
Visa information must be provided to match against the search criteria.
The search criteria includes matching against various contact information, bio details or business name.It will determine whether the visa application matches existing entities of concern.

Service Behaviour

Match Strength is used to capture whether each entity match is low, medium or high.
Match strength is determined by the following set of rules:
Why the entity is in the system, e.g. to what type of business event is the entity linked.
Degree of Separation of the applicant, which owns the entity that has been matched from the applicant associated with the event to which the entity is linked.
The amount of time the entity has been identified as being of integrity concern.
Relationship between owner of entity and principal applicant on linked event.

This service is to determine the level of evidence required for a visa applicant. At this stage the service is only being used by students.

This service is designed to support entity matching for IRIS applications through CVoR.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is designed to support entity matching for IRIS applications through CVoR.
It determines the risk level for an application in a request/response asynchronis transaction.

Service Behaviour

Enhancements will be made to the IRIS to support risk checking against CVOR / GOIS. This will be achieved by routing ICCI format messages via the ESB, with the ESB transforming the new SV607 (Determine Application Risk) messages to SV415 (Match Risk Profile) service requests against CVOR. IRIS changes to hold additional OIS data on SDP files within IRIS. IRIS changes to display results of risk check to users. IRIS to provide support for manually triggering a risk check via the IRIS UI.

models.description: This file is a core file and reused by multipe sevices

Service Usage

eBusiness Attachments is a web application involved in the eLodgement process. Visa Applicants who have lodged eVisa online applications can attach files that are required to progress the assessment of their application.
models.readme:
Service Usage

eBusiness Attachments is a web application involved in the eLodgement process. Visa Applicants who have lodged eVisa online applications can attach files that are required to progress the assessment of their application.

A batch process (EVITRM) sends attached files to be stored into TRIM. An attribute on the request to TRIM, informs TRIM where to store the document. This attribute is the Business Context Container ID. Prior to sending to TRIM, EVITRM requests the Business Context Container ID from the Visa processing system to which the related Visa application was lodged.

Service Behaviour

Business Context Container ID must exist for successful completion of this sequence. Agreed design is that GVP will create a Business Context Container ID at lodgement. Attachments can only be created post-lodgement, so the Business Context Container ID should always exist. Current interaction with ICSE allows for the case where Business Context Container ID does not exist. This requires attachment processing to retrieve a new Business Context Container ID from TRIM when does not exist in ICSE and then update ICSE. If GVP is not guaranteeing the existence of a Business Context Container ID post-lodgement, then additional services will be required for these purposes.
If GVP has not received a Business Context Container ID at the time of this request, it should respond accordingly. Expected processing is that GVP will manage the creation of a Business Context Container ID, eBusiness batch processes will continue to periodically request the file number until it succeeds. Attachments will not be lodged to TRIM and therefore not be available in the GVP UI until GVP has successfully created the Business Context Container ID in TRIM.
GVP will create one business context container per application, at lodgement time. If a business context container was not created at lodgement time, due to system error then GVP will create a business context container when this service is called.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Flow

ESB DP (HTTPS) implementation of Retrieve Business Context Container.
Provided by ICSE, consumed by sfp-attachments from BR02.
Retrieves an Application's Business Context Container ID from the application processing system if one exists at time of service invoke.
Service Pattern- Synchronous
Input - Service Consumer, Business Service Identifier
Output - Information Messages, Warning Messages, Business Context Container Id, Business Context Type, Business Context Sub type, Business Context Id, Applicants List
Each Person Applicant will have: Role Code, Party Identifiers, Bio Details (Given Name, Family Name, Name Type, DOB, COB), Citizenships.
Each Organisation Applicant will have: Role Code, Party Identifiers, Bio Details (Org Name, Name Type).
Service behavior:
(1) In rare occasions, the service will not return the BCC Id (this can happen when the TRIM service invoked by ICSE to create the BCC Id fails or times out)
(2) The service will return all applicants in the application, including organisations, regardless of whether the BCC is present or not
(3) The ICSE permission request number will always be returned under BusinessContextContainerId, regardless of whether the BCC is present or not; similarly, the BusinessContextType and subtype will also always be returned
(4) The possible options for BusinessContextType are: VISA, NOMINATION, SPONSORSHIP, CITIZENSHIP
(5) The possible options for BusinessContextSubtype are: CITIZENSHIP (for CITIZENSHIP ContextType) and ASSESSMENT (for all other ContextTypes)

models.description:
Service Usage

This service will send notification messages from DHUB to Online Account when an update occurs to a Business Service's Transaction Status or Correspondence Details.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service will send notification messages from DHUB to Online Account when an update occurs to a Business Service's Transaction Status or Correspondence Details.
DHUB, upon receiving an update to a Business Service's Transaction Status via the existing business service update APIs or upon receiving an update to a Business Service's Correspondence information via EV30 will trigger DHUB to send a Notify Business Service Update Request message to Online Account containing information about the Business Service such as the Business Service's Transaction Status (Finalised) and Correspondence Information such as, Correspondence Sent time, Description, Delivery Channel, BCC, Document ID and Correspondence Address/Contact details

Service Behaviour

  • if CDH client matching has not been executed and no client identifier is provided, execute client matching
  • add applicant to business service
  • execute auto processing for the added applicant: Health check, Biometrics check, CMAL check, Risk check, Security Referral, evaluate auto grant, application allocation. Note that not all these setps are required for all types of business services

models.description:
Service Usage

The service provides the ability to perform validate check whether a given transaction can proceed with payment from Online Account.
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service provides the ability to perform validate check whether a given transaction can proceed with payment from Online Account.

This service is triggered from Online Account to eVisa/ELP.

Provider Sequence List:

  1. Online Account requests ELP/eVisas to validate the application
  2. eVisa/ELP requests Visa Processing System (ICSE/GVP) to prevalidate the requested message.
  3. eVisa/ELP returns success/fail to Online Account based on whehter the transactio passed validation or not

Service Behaviour

Online Account sends a service request to eVisa/ELP to validate a given transaction to determine whether it can proceed with payment.
Once eVisa/ELP performs the transaction validation check in Visa Processing System, it returns validation success/fail to Online Account based on whether the transaction passed validation or not

It is an synchronous service with request and response.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

models.description:
Service Usage

This service provides the ability to import electronic/paper Application Summary from CDH where lodgement was either from Online Lodgement, Visa Processing System (ICSE/GVP/IRIS)
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service provides the ability to import electronic/paper Application Summary from CDH where lodgement was either from Online Lodgement, Visa Processing System (ICSE/GVP/IRIS)
This service is triggered from Online Account to CDH to allow the client to retrieve application at Post Lodgement still progress i.e not finalise yet to check for the application status, complete Online Health form, attach document etc.
CDH will find the application in DHUB and advise Online Account finding result ie Application and related correspondence summary information.
The matching will be based on TRN, Client DOB/Business Registration Id and Passport Number.

Service Behaviour

Online Account will send a request to CDH to import the application summary.
CDH will find the associated Post Lodgement application and is YET to finalise for the requested client information and return the transaction details if match otherwise return an error message.
The matching will be based on TRN, DOB/Business Registration Id and Passport Number.

It is a synchronous service with request and response.

The provider of this service is CDH.
The service is synchronous.

There are two types of inputs in the request:
The business service id to uniquely identify a transaction (TRN or PRID).
Primary applicant data to verify that the located application can be returned in the response (DOB, & passport details)

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Flow

This service is part of the scope of implementing import application functionality as part of the online account project for CR12.
Users will be provided with the ability to import applications (including paper).

Users will be asked to complete a simple form, the data they enter will be sent to CDH in the request of this new service.

CDH will attempt to find the application and validate the applicant details entered. If a match is found then Business Service information is provided back in the response of this new service.

Request Data
The user will be asked for the following which will be populated in the request:
A business service identifier (TRN or PRID)
Primary applicant details including (applicant with role type of 1):
o Birth Date
o Travel document Id & country of issue

Response Data
If a match is found the snapshot of information in the response would be exactly what the CR10 SV497 notification request contains with the addition of the applicant data and transaction lodgement date.

Service Usage

This service allows for additional applicants to be added to an application (visa or citizenship applications) after lodgement. After a visa or citizenship application has been lodged, clients can add additional applicants to the lodged application before a decision has been made on their original application and if the visa or citizenship allows additional applicants to be added after lodgement.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service allows for additional applicants to be added to an application (visa or citizenship applications) after lodgement. After a visa or citizenship application has been lodged, clients can add additional applicants to the lodged application before a decision has been made on their original application and if the visa or citizenship allows additional applicants to be added after lodgement.
For a given business service, this service will add the applicants provided in the service request.

Service Behaviour

  • if CDH client matching has not been executed and no client identifier is provided, execute client matching
  • add applicant to business service
  • execute auto processing for the added applicant: Health check, Biometrics check, CMAL check, Risk check, Security Referral, evaluate auto grant, application allocation. Note that not all these setps are required for all types of business services

Service Usage

This service is used to notify subscribers when action is required on a visa or citizenship application. models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to notify subscribers when action is required on a visa or citizenship application. The action required can be at the application (eg. payment required) or role (eg. biometrics required) level. In the case of a role action, it will always be in the context of a single application.

Service Behaviour

The service contains additional client information which is used to create a ghost record in online account in the instance where they do not know the client associated with the role identifier. This is common in cases where applicants have been added to an application post lodgement.

Service Flow

  1. The publisher sends a SV636 request message to the ESB.
  2. The ESB responds to the publisher with an generic acknowledgement message.
  3. The ESB sends the SV636 request message to the consumers.

Transformation

ICSE notifications use the ICSE provider message ICSENotification.xsd. This is transformed on the ESB into SV626 enterprise XML.

Referral Sub Type

Status
Departmental Officer
o Given Name
o Family Name
o ID
Created Date
Reason for Referral
Planned Completion Date
Source Business Service
o Service Type
o Service Sub Type
o Service Sate Code
Recipient Business Service
o Service Type
o Service Sub Type
o Service Sate Code

A consumer of this service relies on ESB for an assured delivery and does not accept a response back.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services in the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

  1. An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the CreateExceptionReferralRequest service on the ESB;
  2. ESB passes the XML message unchanged through to CCMD&S
  3. No response message is supplied
    1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
    There are no alternative flows as no response is given and therefore no error is returned.

Transformation

No Transformations are performed.

No state management required.

Service Composition

This service is a not composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services in the Service Portfolio. This service needs only one Perception provider call to complete.

Service Flow

The detail of the flow is as follows:
Service Consumer invokes service with CreateCitizenshipTestParticipantRequest input message on ESB
ESB sends the CreateCitizenshipTestParticipantRequest message to perception
Perception executes the message transaction and returns the CreateCitizenshipTestParticipantResponse output message back to ESB
ESB returns CreateCitizenshipTestParticipantResponse output message to Service Consumer

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service allows the results of a Citizenship Test Result to be broadcast to consumers once the test has been completed.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service allows the results of a Citizenship Test Result to be broadcast to consumers once the test has been completed.
The execution of this system will occur once the client has completed the Citizenship test (in the case of an online test) or the officer has entered the test scores (in the case of a paper based test).

Service Behaviour

This service supports only the broadcasting of the citizenship test result once the score has been calculated. For online tests this will be immediately following completion of the test and for paper based tests will be once the officer has entered the test scores.
A consumer of this service provides the following data:
The Citizenship Appointment ID
The Perception System User ID
The date and time the test was completed or submitted.
The Test Type.
The Result of Pass, Fail or Fail - did not pass mandatory.
A consumer of this service receives one of the following types of data:
An acknowledgement that the Test result has been received successfully.
or
A single error message as specified in section :
A consumer of this service is assumed to have the privileges to perform the recording of a test result.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

CCMDS

Service Composition

This service is a not composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services in the Service Portfolio. This service needs only one Perception provider call to complete.

Service Flow

The detail of the flow is as follows:
Service Provider (Perception) sends the RecordCitizenshipTestResultRequest input message on ESB
ESB returns a success message once it has successfully received the message from Perception (simulating an asynchronous message)
ESB sends the RecordCitizenshipTestResultRequest message to the CTMS portal.
CTMS executes the message transaction and returns the RecordCitizenshipTestResultResponse output message back to ESB.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to request or update a client appointment with the department. The service can be used to request various appointment types (eg. Citizenship or ABF Cargo).

Service Behaviour

This service allows the consumer to request for an appointment schedule. The consumer may request for certain preferences within the request, for example, appointment before certain date or preferred weekend day.

Service Flow

  1. The consumer sends a request to the ESB. 2. The ESB transforms the message into an outbound JSON message. 3. The ESB sends the JSON message to the MSG gatway. 4. The MSG gateway makes the REST call.

The service supports both synchronous and asynchronous patterns.

Transformation

Transformation exists on the ESB between ICSE provider and enterprise messages. Enterprise messages are transformed into JSON messages on the ESB.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service is used to create electronic storage containers which are required to store electronic document records in. The service current supports the creation of Administration File (ADF), Business Context (BCC), Client File (CLF), No Further Action and Inbox containers.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to create electronic storage containers which are required to store electronic document records in. The service current supports the creation of Administration File (ADF), Business Context (BCC), Client File (CLF), No Further Action and Inbox containers.

Service Behaviour

This service utilises a container bank solution which is a sub component of the RKS system. The container bank stores pre-defined containers which can be allocated in isolation from the provider system. When the container bank receives a request and the ServiceAction/SyncContainerCreationFlag flag is set to "true", the RKS will search and match on the criteria specified by the consumer (container type, security classification and access control). Once matched, the container is set to "allocated" in the container bank. There is then periodic syncronisation between the container bank and the provider system.

Service Flow

Normal Flow:

  1. Consumer invokes CreateElectronicContainer on ESB
  2. ESB transforms CreateElectronicContainerRequest to CreateContainerRequest
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeepingService.createContainer() on RecordKeeping component using CreateContainerRequest.
  4. Record Keeping Service relates the created container to other related information records using the list of provided information record ids.
  5. If No error occurs RKS.createContainer creates a new Container and returns an ContainerId in CreateContainerResponse.
  6. The ESB transforms CreateContainerResponse to CreateElectronicContainerResponse
  7. The ESB returns CreateElectronicContainerResponse to the consumer.

Alternate Flow 1 (Security Error):

  1. Consumer invokes CreateElectronicContainer on ESB
  2. ESB transforms CreateElectronicContainerRequest to CreateContainerRequest
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeepingService.createContainer() on RecordKeeping component using CreateContainerRequest.
  4. RKS returns a security error if the user invoking the service does not have rights to create Container.
  5. The ESB returns SV249.MSG-E02 to the consumer.

Alternate Flow 2 (Container Already Exists):

  1. Consumer invokes CreateElectronicContainer on ESB
  2. ESB transforms CreateElectronicContainerRequest to CreateContainerRequest
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeepingService.createContainer() on RecordKeeping component using CreateContainerRequest.
  4. The RKS returns a ContainerId and the response also contains a warning message
  5. The ESB maps the RKS response to CreteElectronicContainerResponse and returns the ContainerId and warning message to the consumer.

Alternate Flow 3 (Database Unavailable):

  1. Consumer invokes CreateElectronicContainer on ESB
  2. ESB transforms CreateElectronicContainerRequest to CreateContainerRequest
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeepingService.createContainer() on RecordKeeping component using CreateContainerRequest.
  4. RKS returns a system error if problems with database connection occur.
  5. The ESB returns SV249.MSG-E01 to the consumer.

Alternate Flow 5 (Related Records Error):

  1. Consumer invokes CreateElectronicContainer on ESB
  2. ESB transforms CreateElectronicContainerRequest to CreateContainerRequest
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeepingService.createContainer() on RecordKeeping component using CreateContainerRequest.
  4. Record Keeping Service creates the container successfully.
  5. Record Keeping Service encounters exception while relating the created container to other related information records using the list of provided information record ids.
  6. RKS returns successfully created containers Container Id with a warning message, with RWNG00210 code, giving reason of exception while relating container to other related information records.
  7. The ESB transforms CreateContainerResponse to CreateElectronicContainerResponse
  8. The ESB returns CreateElectronicContainerResponse to the consumer.

Transformation

Transformation exists on the ESB between enterprise and RKS provider messages

models.readme:
Service Usage

The service modifies electronic container metadata pertaining to the location of a paper file.The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when the custodian and/or the physical location of a paper file changes. The consumers needs to provide title, current location and phsycial flag. An acknowledgement that the modification was successful or an enterprise error detailing why the update was unsuccessful is returned in the response.

Note: The Service will allow input of any value for changing the current Location. However, it is likely that this will only work for exact matches where there are no duplicates. It is currently out of scope for GVP to build a table of likely locations, and performance is likely to prevent delivery of a list of possible locations from TRIM to the portal

models.description:
Service Usage

This service uses the Enterprise Correspondence Service (ECS) to generate standard correspondence using information from the message. In particular, this service will:
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service uses the Enterprise Correspondence Service (ECS) to generate standard correspondence using information from the message. In particular, this service will:
Gather data (if necessary);
Generate correspondence; and
Email the correspondence.
Although the service is synchronous in responding with a correspondence id, the actual sending of the correspondence is asynchronous.

Service Behaviour

This service generates standard correspondence in the following steps:
The consumer calls the service with information that will allow ECS to generate and dispatch the correspondence;
The ESB will validate the message;
If ESB determines the message is erroneous it will send an error message back to the consumer; for example, if the XML is not compliant to the schema;
If ESB determines the message is correctly formed it will call an ECS API;
ECS will validate the template data and, if erroneous, will send an error message back to the consumer;
If ECS determines the message is correct it will send a success status back to ESB
If ECS determines the message is incorrect it will send an error status back to ESB
ESB will return the status to the consumer.
It is important to understand that the job of this service is to deliver the necessary data to ECS for it to generate and dispatch stock correspondence, but not to wait on the generation and dispatch of the correspondence. A success message back to the consumer only indicates that ECS has received the message and will process it at some stage; it does not indicate the success or otherwise of ECSs attempts to generate and dispatch the correspondence.
The service uses SOAP/XML. A consumer of this service receives an Enterprise status message.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

Service Composition

Service Flow

The Service Consumer which invokes the Dispatch Stock Correspondence service on the ESB;
If the consumers message is not well-formed then ESB will send an error to the consumer;
If the consumers message is well-formed according to the ESB then the DispatchStockCorrespondenceRequest message is transformed into the AutogenerateAndDispatchRequest message for ECS;
If ECS have a problem processing the message an error is sent back to the ESB;
If ECS can further process the message a success status is sent back to ESB. The success status indicates that ECS can process the message further and does not indicate that the message has either been generated into correspondence or that the correspondence has been dispatched.
The status is then returned to the consumer. If the consumer receives a success status then they should check later that the correspondence was generated and dispatched.
Outside of this service an event will be returned to the consumer informing them of the actual outcome of the correspondence, e.g. Email dispatched.
Note: The ECS web service XSD will not be one-to-one aligned with the SV322 XSD. Transformation will be required at the ESB level for:
Request message (transform from ESB version to ECS version). Should be limited to changing attribute names. Values to be unchanged.
Response message (transform from ECS version to ESB version). May require transformation on the error codes, but otherwise values to be unchanged.
Please refer to the ESB micro document for transformation details.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
ESB transforms errors into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return ENTR00007 to the consumer.

Transformation

Service State Management Decisions

No state management.

models.readme:
Service Usage

This event notifies users of any change to the biographic's or the documents with the associated biographic's leaving the changes to other party updates such as religion, ethnicity and marital status and alert flags as un notified. This should only be used over other events when it's the change to biographic's and the documents which is of interest. This includes merges and splits if new names etc are added or removed.
It's also worth noting that it's usually proof of identity Documents and in the case of immigration a large proportion of passports and other travel documents that is held in CDH but is not exclusive to these. Other documents can be notified including driver's licences and other non-POI documents. The document type in the payload should be used as a reference for all expected documents.

models.readme:
Service Usage

The service is used to notify changes to a specific subset of client information that is maintained by CDH (Client Data Hub). The published message will only contain the items of client information that have changed.
The service will be used:

  1. To asynchronously notify a subscribed party when Client information changes in the CDH.

Service Variants

Service Composition

CDH will notify this event when any changes are made to Client information in the CDH from upstream systems, including ICSE, IRIS (C-IRIS) and TRIPS. The event is implemented as an asynchronous transaction.
CDH will publish general information about the Event Header such as:

  • Event Code - This field will contain the hard-coded value EV012
  • Notification Date Time
  • Added By User Id
  • Event Date
  • Event Recorded Date (if applicable)
  • Event Additional Information
    CDH will publish only the subset of client information that has changed.
    Data includes:
    Citizenship Details
    Contact Address
    Contact Email
    Contact Fax
    Contact Telephone
    Contact Person
    Contact Person Address
    Current Visa Details
    Ethnicity
    MaritalStatus
    Party Identifier
    Party Information
    PartyOfInterestNote
    Person Biodata
    Person Language
    Related Party Person Details
    Religion
    Address

Service Usage

The service uses the event notification pattern described in the Service Modelling Patterns document and is realised using the existing service SV258.
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service uses the event notification pattern described in the Service Modelling Patterns document and is realised using the existing service SV258.

Service Behaviour

The service is used to publish status information that relates to a business dealing update. Once CDH is updated it will trigger EV017 to the broker which will then, in turn, signal the various subscribers. If the subscriber is CCMDS only provide notification when the Party has an active SCID (Siebel Client ID) and where the create/modify did not originate from Siebel.

When the subscriber is CMAL only provide notification where there has been a GVP application that has been created or updated.

Service Variants

The event has no variant. It is based on the publish-subscribe notification framework that can be used to publish events to different notification consumers.

The EV017-v04.0 Notify Party Business Dealing Update event requires the following publishers:

  • CDH (Client Data Hub)

This event has the following notification consumers:

  • CCMD&S (Compliance Case Management Detention and Settlement);
  • CMAL

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

The service is triggered when a partys record changes or is updated with regard to:

  • Case and Service Summary
  • Business dealings that including:
    -- Visa Applications
    -- Visa Cancellations
    -- Citizenship
    -- Sponsorship applications and agreement
    -- Nominations
    -- AOS
    -- Health
    -- Monitoring
    -- Other
    -- Visa entitlement verification
    -- Enforcement
  • Visa History (Grants) (XBusinessDealingCategory = 99)
  • Border Referrals
  • Security Referrals

CDH will publish a business centric view of the event, which will primarily be the business dealing category and the id relating to the business. For some business dealings, such as those involve additional information. Only active identifiers will be sent by EV017. Both active and Inactive roles and relationships will be sent by EV017.

Service Flow

The service will be used in the following circumstances:-

  1. To notify consumers of updates to business dealings in CDH.

NOTE: Messages to SIEBEL will be filtered as follows:

SIEBEL will only receive ICSE Updates for PV (Business dealing Type - Protection) OR any updates from IRIS.

Service Usage

This service retrieves the price of a specified product. The master list of these product prices is maintained in the DIAC implementation of SAP, and contains applicable prices in multiple currencies, for receipting purposes throughout the organisation.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service retrieves the price of a specified product. The master list of these product prices is maintained in the DIAC implementation of SAP, and contains applicable prices in multiple currencies, for receipting purposes throughout the organisation.
The service is expected to be used by visa processing officers to assist them during the Visa application processing, by allowing the price of an item to be displayed. The price will be the one applicable at a specified point in time, and will be returned in all currencies applicable for the location provided in the service request.
The request will contain the identifier of the product for which a price is required, the Location for which returned currencies should be applicable, and the date at which the returned price should be relevant (referred to as the Key date).
Each office has a limited set of currencies that may be proffered, at its location, as payment for a DIAC product. In the initial implementation, US dollars (USD) will always be returned as one of the returned set of currencies.
This service is part of a suite of revenue and receipting services being delivered by the Revenue Receipting project. It will support DIAC revenue streams that can be used in DIAC offices, both onshore and offshore. The functionality it delivers will initially be utilised by the Generic Visa Portal.

Service Behaviour

This service retrieves a price from the SAP based product catalogue. The price returned will be the one relevant at the provided date (Key date), and will be delivered in terms of all currencies applicable for the identified Location.
The retrieved data consists of:
Product description Material description - SAP description
Price A list of the product price in all currencies
applicable for the Location.
The list is pairs of Currency code and the amount in that currency.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer identifying a unique node (branch point) in product catalogue tree, and an office location for currency selection.

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the RetrieveProductPrice service on the ESB.
ESB invokes the SAP.retrieveProductPrice service on SAP, passing RetrieveProductPriceRequest.xml without change.
Primary provider SAP executes the SAP.retrieveProductPrice service and returns RetrieveProductPriceResponse.xml to the ESB.
ESB returns the RetrieveProductPriceResponse.xml to the Service Consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
Primary provider SAP returns a specific error code to the ESB; see section 4 of this document for a full listing of Return Codes and Messages.
ESB transforms error code into the relevant Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the ESB raises an error before or while attempting to contact the primary provider, it will respond to the consumer with the relevant Enterprise Error payload. See section 4 of this document for a full listing of Return Codes and Messages.

Service State Management Decisions

Provider system errors
If the provider system returns an error code at any stage of the service execution, the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer. This service will not return partial response messages.
Invalid Product or Location identifier provided
If the SAP component of this service is called using an invalid Product identifier, a Departmental Location identifier, or an invalid Key Date, the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer.

Service Usage

This service enables a user to associate a health case to a visa application. A Health Case can only be associated to one Visa Application at any single point in time. If a consumer needs to associate a Health Case with a different Visa Application, SV037-v01.0 should be used to disassociate the Health Case from the current Visa Application before invoking the Associate Health Case to Visa Application service.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service enables a user to associate a health case to a visa application. A Health Case can only be associated to one Visa Application at any single point in time. If a consumer needs to associate a Health Case with a different Visa Application, SV037-v01.0 should be used to disassociate the Health Case from the current Visa Application before invoking the Associate Health Case to Visa Application service.
This service must be invoked with a valid Visa Application identifier and Health Case identifier.
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is reviewing a health case when making an assessment on the eligibility for a partys entitlement for a specific visa application. They will be required to link a health case to a visa if:
The visa application currently has no health case associated to it.
The visa application had an incorrect health case associated to it, which they have previously unlinked.
A consumer of this service must possess the required privileges to perform the association.

Service Behaviour

This service associates a single health case for a party to a specific visa application. The service will ensure that a single health case is not associated with more than one visa application, and that the Visa Application that the health case is being associated actually exists. The service will also ensure that the party associated with the health case is the same party associated with the visa application.
If the visa application that the health case is to be associated to has been decided, the service will still proceed with the association process.
The service will allow a health case to be associated to a visa application even if the health case itself has been finalised.

Service Dependencies

This service requires that the Consumer has already called SV125-v01.0 Retrieve Health Case List in order to find a valid Health Case identifier and SV010-v01.0 Retrieve Visa Application to find a valid Visa Application Identifier.

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services in the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

Service Consumer invokes service on ESB.
ESB transforms AssociateHealthCaseRequest into COBOL copybook ICSVLINKHAPRSRVCI and sends it to ICSE. ICSE executes CICS transaction and returns COBOL copybook ICSVLINKHAPRSRVCO to ESB.
ESB transforms COBOL copybook ICSVLINKHAPRSRVC_O into AssociateHealthCaseResponse.
ESB returns AssociateHealthCaseResponse to Consumer.
Potential Response Message Labels
SV036.MSG-E01
SV036.MSG-E02
SV036.MSG-E03
SV036.MSG-E04

models.description:
Service Usage

This service allows the user to create a health case for a specific person. The number of Health Cases that can be created for a person is not restricted by this service.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service allows the user to create a health case for a specific person. The number of Health Cases that can be created for a person is not restricted by this service.
A Health Case can be created without a corresponding Visa Application. The association of a Health Case to a Visa Application can be completed in the future by using SV036-v01.0 Associate Health Case to Visa Application.
The Health Case can be created with a corresponding Health Note and with zero or more Health Requirements. A user of this service must have the required privileges to create a Health Case
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is making an assessment on the eligibility for a partys entitlement for a specific visa application.
A health case is created for one of the following reasons:
When there is a Visa Application for a party that does not have health requirements, and the client submits a Visa Variation that results in Health Requirements (X-Ray and/or medical) it will necessitate a VPO to initiate a health case creation if there is no health case that is currently linked to this visa.
MAL alerts can affect health and necessitate manual creation of a health case.
An examination date for a Health Requirement should only be specified and will be deemed valid if the Health Requirement contains at least one Health Requirement Status of Received (Code value 45).
This service can also indicate that the Health Assessment Portal is the master of the record it is sending to ICSE. ICSE then simply becomes a reference only for these records and may restrict or warn access when editing. The Service provides the ability for the Health Portal to indicate it is the master of the record.

Service Behaviour

This service will create a health case with optionally one Health Note and with a collection of health requirements.
An error message will be returned if a user of the service does not have the required privileges to create a Health Case. The appropriate error message will also be returned if the Health Case is not created with a valid person id.
If the Health Case is created with a Visa Application Identifier, the Health Case will be associated to the Visa Application by the service provider. An error message may be returned if the person associated with the Visa Application is not the same person associated with the Health Case
A success return code will be returned if service has successfully created the Health Case.

Service Composition

This service is a composite service i.e. it is composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Create Health Case service on the ESB;
If the CID is not supplied ESB invokes SV288 to retrieve the CID from CDH
ESB transforms CreateHealthCaseRequest into the ICSE HealthMaintenanceRequest
ESB calls the ICSE Health Maintenance API
ICSE returns the HealthMaintenanceResponse
ESB transforms the HealthMaintenanceResponse to a CreateHealthCaseReponse message, which is returned to the consumer
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following execution flow describes the process that is to be taken if the CID does not exist in CDH.
Service Consumer invokes service on ESB
If the CID is not supplied, ESB invokes SV288 to retrieve the CID from CDH.
SV288 contains no active CID, ESB returns an Error stating that no active CID exists on the record.

Service State Management Decisions

Provider system errors
If either provider system returns an error code at any stage of the service execution, the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer. This service will not return partial response messages.
Inactive ICSE identifier used
When the ICSE service is called using an inactive/end dated identifier (i.e. an error is thrown by ICSE) the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service retrieves all the detailed information pertaining to a health case for a given health case identifier (HealthCaseId).
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service retrieves all the detailed information pertaining to a health case for a given health case identifier (HealthCaseId).
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is making an assessment on the eligibility for a partys entitlement for a specific visa application. The user may require the outputs of this service to perform health assessment activities as part of the process of reviewing an application.
A user of this service must have valid authorization to view all data elements that is returned by the service.

Service Behaviour

The service retrieves health case information for a given health case Id. The service can return details of a health case that has been finalised. Hence the retrieval of a Health Case and its associated entities are not restricted by any date boundaries.
The service returns attributes associated with a:
Health Case
Health Case Requirement(s)*
Health Case Status
Health Outcome(s)*
Health Note(s)*
Visa Summary*

  • Indicates an optional entity. I.e. The Health Case does not require these entities for its existence.
    Note: A visa summary is returned only if the Health Case is associated to a visa application. A Health Case can only be associated to one visa application at any point in time (See SV036-v01.0) therefore only a single visa summary will be returned. The visa summary includes the unique visa application identifier and its associated latest milestone information. Also the service code and the milestone information will only be returned by the ICSE API if the mode is Health.
    The statuses of various health requirements are currently stored in two separate repositories. In order to retrieve the complete set of statuses for a health case, the service interacts with two distinct service providers. See 1.3 Service Providers.
    The service will return an error if a user of this service does not have access to view the complete data set.
    A warning will be returned if the service could not create the response in its entirety because the secondary service provider could not fulfil its duties or the provider repositories are out of sync.
    This service is being changed to include MOC Costs and a prejudicial indictor. The service is also being changed to use XML rather than copybook.

Service Composition

ICSE is responsible for returning one health case summary for a specific Health Case.
It is responsible for returning the following data set
Health Case Summary attributes (See 1.1.4.1.4 Variant Message Object Model)
A summary of the Latest Significant Health Outcome
If a user has insufficient privileges to view the data contained within the response. ICSE should return the appropriate error message.

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Retrieve Health Case Details service on the ESB;
ESB transforms RetrieveHealthCaseSummaryRequest into RetrieveApplicationRequest and sends it to ICSE
ICSE gathers the health cases and returns RetrieveApplicationResponse
ESB transforms RetrieveApplicationResponse into RetrieveHealthCaseSummaryResponse. At this point the response is partially complete.
ESB performs complex logic
ESB creates eHealth request message RetrieveEHealthHealthCaseDetailsRequest and sends request to eHealth if the provider code is in 2, 5, 6 or 7.
eHealth executes retrieval function and returns RetrieveEHealthHealthCaseDetailsResponse XML to ESB.
ESB merges results
ESB invokes SV001.v01-1.
ESB creates searchPartyRequest message
ESB sets searchPartyRequest.PartyIdentifier.Identifier = RetrieveHealthCaseDetailsResponse.PersonId
ESB sets searchPartyRequest.PartyIdentifier.IdentifierType = CID
ESB sends SV001.v01-1 request
CDH executes transaction CDH-002 and ESB receives response SearchPartyResponse
ESB extracts enterprise party identifier from response ESB returns RetrieveHealthCaseDetailsResponse to Consumer
The eHealth response is merged into the RetrieveHealthCaseSummaryResponse
ESB returns RetrieveHealthCaseSummaryResponse to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
ESB transforms ICSE Error into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return SV106.MSG-E00 to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 3 (AF3)
Describes the execution path that occurs when the primary provider (ICSE) returns with one or more warning or informational messages
ESB includes all warning or informational messages within response payload.
ESB returns RetrieveHealthCaseDetailsResponse to Consumer
Informational and Warning messages that are returned by ICSE that are to be returned to the consumer and do not stop the execution of the service
Alternate Flow 4 (AF4)
This alternate flow traces the same execution path as described in the successful Service Flow. However, all unsuccessful return codes / messages that are returned by eHealth are to be categorised as warnings. As such, the ESB should map the code and include the warning within the payload.
Alternate Flow 3 (AF3)
The alternate flow depicts the execution path that occurs when a HealthRequirement inconsistency is discovered between the result set returned by the primary provider (ICSE) or the secondary provider (eHealth). That is, where the ESB detects that there is a missing HealthRequirement in one of the returned result sets.
ESB calls ICSE and transforms the response into the health details message
ESB performs complex logic
ESB creates eHealth request message RetrieveEHealthHealthCaseDetailsRequest and sends request to eHealth.
eHealth executes retrieval function and returns XML to ESB.
ESB executes complex transformation to merge results
ESB detects that either ICSE or eHealth has a missing HealthRequirement
ESB includes new Warning message and code that informs the consumer which provider result set the inconsistency was detected within.
ESB returns RetrieveHealthCaseDetailsResponse to Consumer
The following warning messages are to be used when an inconsistency between result sets is detected within the ESB
NOTE: Within a single provider scenario. If the response is received after the service consumer has timed out. The ESB is to still follow one of the defined service flows. That is, the response that would have been returned if a timeout didnt occur has to still be returned to the consumer. Therefore, it will be left up to the consumer to handle the delayed / timed out responses. However, within a multiple service provider scenario the ESB will decide whether to return the partially completed response or disregard the entire transaction. This decision has to be made on a service by service basis. In the above situation the ESB returns the partially completed response when the second service provider times out.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service allows a user to modify a specific Health Case and its associated entities (Health Requirement(s), Health Requirement Status and Health Note(s)).
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service allows a user to modify a specific Health Case and its associated entities (Health Requirement(s), Health Requirement Status and Health Note(s)).
A Health Case can be updated if it is associated to a Visa Application that has been decided. It can also be reversed if the health event had been previously finalised.
The request should only be populated with the information that a user wants to change / update within a Health Case. There are no restrictions on the number of Health Requirements or Health Requirement Statuses that can be associated (appended) to a Health Case. Health Requirements and statues can still be changed or added to a Health Case when the Health Case has been finalised.
The service does not support a delete of any entity that can be modified by this service.
The Visa Application Identifier specified within the modify request message should be the same identifier that is currently associated with the specific Health Case. It should be noted that specifying a different Visa Application Identifier will not result in a new Visa Application to Health Case association. A consumer should use SV037-v01.0 to disassociate a Health Case from a Visa Application, and subsequently use SV036-v01.0 to associate a different Visa Application to the Health Case if the consumer wants the Health Case to be linked to a different Visa Application.
A user of this service must have the required privileges to update a Health Case.
A Health Case is considered to be modified under the following circumstances:
Health Case Notes are added/amended
Health Case is finalised
Health Case details changed
o NOTE: The Health Case Id, Case Identifier and Visa Application Id cannot be modified.
o The standard audit attribute, UpdatedTimestamp should not be modified.
Health Requirement is created or updated
Health Requirement Status is created or updated
Health Outcome is created or updated
Health Requirement Notes are added/amended
Reverse Finalised Health Event Flag

An examination date for a Health Requirement should only be specified and will be deemed valid if the Health Requirement contains at least one Health Requirement Status of Received (Code value 45).

The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is making an assessment

Service Behaviour

The service updates the details associated with a Health Case. It will attempt to update the Health Case with all information that has been passed to it within the request message. Entity identifier attributes, such as the Health Case Id, Visa Application Id and Case Identifier will not be updated.
All Health Requirements, Health Requirement Statuses, Health Outcomes and Health Notes that have been included within the modification request will either be updated if they currently exist or created if they dont.
The service will check to ensure that the Visa Application Id passed in via the request is the same Visa Application Id currently associated with the Health Case. If the Visa Application Id is found to be different, the service will return an error.
A user of this service must have the required privileges to modify a health case. An error message may be returned if the service determines that the user is not authorised to modify a Health Case.

A success return code will be returned if the service has successfully modified the Health Case.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

  1. An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Modify Health Case service on the ESB;
  2. ESB transforms ModifyHealthCaseRequest into a HealthMaintenanceRequest and sends it to ICSE
  3. ICSE executes a CICS transactions and returns a response
  4. ESB transforms HealthMaintenanceResponse into a ModifyHealthCaseResponse to the consumer

Service State Management Decisions

Provider system errors
If either provider system returns an error code at any stage of the service execution, the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer. This service will not return partial response messages.
Inactive ICSE identifier used
When the ICSE service is called using an inactive/end dated identifier (i.e. an error is thrown by ICSE) the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer.

Service Usage

This service is now decommissioned.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is now decommissioned.

This service retrieves a collection of health case summaries pertaining to a party or, retrieves a single health case summary for a particular health case. The summary information provided enables a user to determine if they wish to retrieve a health case it its entirety. (See SV106-v01.0)

A consumer of this service must ensure that the service is invoked with either a Health Case Identifier or a Party Identifier. The service will ensure that the consumer is authorized to retrieve and thus view the information that is returned by the service.

The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is making an assessment on the eligibility for a partys entitlement for a specific visa application.

Service Behaviour

The service retrieves a list of one or more health case summaries for a unique party identifier or a single health case summary for a specific health case identifier.

The service will return summaries for all health cases associated to a party even if the health case has been finalised. Likewise, a consumer can choose to view the summary for a specific finalised health case. Hence, the consumers request is not restricted by any date boundaries. Summaries are also not constrained if the health case is not associated to a visa application.

This service does not return any health notes associated with the health case, the health cases health requirements or outcomes.

The summary information returned by the service includes:
Skeleton Health Case Details (See Service Message Object Model for complete attribute listing)
Summary of the Latest Significant Outcome excluding outcome related Health Notes

If the service cannot return all health case summaries associated with a given person, due to restrictions with response payload size. A warning message will be returned to the consumer signalling that the result set is incomplete.

Payload Restrictions
Health Case Summary = Maximum 20 instances

Furthermore, if a user does not have access to the information contained within the health case summary. The service will return an error message.

A warning will be returned if at least one health case summary cannot be found.

Service Variants

SV125.1 Retrieve Multiple Health Case Lists
Variant Usage
This variant is based on the architectural pattern for simple aggregation of services. Consumers who need to retrieve health case lists for multiple party ids as part of a single process step can use this service to perform all requests to Retrieve Health Case List as a single service call.
The request message consists of a message containing multiple sub-requests, based on the request used in the primary Retrieve Health Case List service. The response message contains a list of responses from the primary SV125.
The consumer must supply a ServiceCorrelationId for request to the underlying SV125 service. These will be paired with the response data, to allow consumers to match requests to responses. Consumers are at liberty to generate ServiceCorrelationId data in any manner they choose.
No more than 15 Retrieve Health Case List requests may be made in a single call to this service.
Variant Behaviour
This service allows consumers to send multiple requests for SV125 in a single request. The Retrieve Multiple Health Case Lists request message will be split into 1 to 15 separate calls to Retrieve Health Case List. Multiple calls will then be made to Retrieve Health Case List. These service calls will be made concurrently, to ensure that the service call is completed with maximum efficiency.
This service is atomic. If one request to the underlying Retrieve Health Case List service fails, a SOAP fault will be returned. No data from any prior successful responses will be returned with the SOAP fault. The SOAP fault will include a message in the additional detail text indicating which request to Retrieve Health Case List resulted in the SOAP fault.
If the consumer attempts to send more than the maximum limit of 15 requests in a single message, the request message will fail validation, and a validation error will be returned.
Variant Service Interface
The variant service interface is defined in the following xsds:
RetrieveMultipleHealthCaseListsRequest.xsd
RetrieveMultipleHealthCaseListsResponse.xsd

Service Dependencies

This service requires that the consumer has already got access to party information, specifically the party Id, or a single unique Health Case Id in order to request a summary for a specific health case.

Service Flow

  1. Service Consumer invokes service on ESB.
  2. ESB invokes service provider CDH-003 to get the ICSE Client Id corresponding to the input party id.
  3. CDH-003 executes and returns CDH-003 Response Object to the ESB. If the Party does not exist in CDH (i.e. CDH Error Type =READERR and Reason Code = 2092 then stop flow and return error message to consumer. (SV002.MSG-E01).
  4. ESB extracts CID from the CDH-003.ResponseObject by searching for an instance of TCRMPartyIdentificationBObj where Identificationtype = lookup value equivalent to ICSE and expiry.date is blank and sets ICSE-005.ClientId. If there is no TCRMPartyIdentificationBObj of that type or there is no instance with a blank expiry date then stop flow and return a message to consumer. (SV105.MSG-E04)
  5. ESB transforms RetrieveHealthCaseListRequest into COBOL copyBook ICSVRTRVHAPRLSTSRVCI and sends it to ICSE.
    a) Note: The client id retrieved from ICSE should be used within the transformation rather than the original input person id.
  6. ICSE executes CICS transaction and returns COBOL copybook ICSVRTRVHAPRLSTSRVCO to ESB.
  7. ESB transforms COBOL copybook ICSVRTRVHAPRLSTSRVCO into RetrieveHealthCaseListResponse.
    a) In addition to Mapping reference document (See Additional Transformation Logic Fig 1)
  8. ESB returns RetrieveHealthCaseListResponse to Consumer.
    Potential Response Message Labels
  • SV125.MSG-E01
  • SV125.MSG-E02
  • SV125.MSG-W01
  • SV125.MSG-W02

models.description:
Service Usage

Note: This service is designed to allow multiple entities to be linked / unlinked from one or more Visa Applications. However, for SFP3, this service only supports the linking / unlinking of Health Cases with Visa Applications. Therefore, this document refers only to Health Cases throughout.
models.readme:
Service Usage

Note: This service is designed to allow multiple entities to be linked / unlinked from one or more Visa Applications. However, for SFP3, this service only supports the linking / unlinking of Health Cases with Visa Applications. Therefore, this document refers only to Health Cases throughout.
This service allows consumers to update the associations between multiple Visa Applications and one or more Health Cases. This service supports both linking and unlinking between Visa Applications and Health Cases within a single service call.
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a Visa Processing Officer (VPO) is reviewing Health Cases associated with Visa Applications, as part of making an assessment of a Partys eligibility. As part of this process, the VPO may need to edit the associations between the Visa Applications and Health Cases.

Service Behaviour

This service supports both linking and unlinking between multiple Visa Applications and multiple Health Cases.
A consumer of this service provides the following data:
One or more Visa Application Ids to which the Health Cases are to be linked or unlinked
One or more Health Case Ids which are to be linked or unlinked from the Visa Applications
For each Health Case, an indicator as to whether the Health Case is to be linked or unlinked from the associated Visa Application
A consumer of this service receives one of the following types of data:
An acknowledgement that the associations in the request between the Visa Applications and the Health Cases was successful
or
A single error message as specified in section 4 Service Enterprise Return Code Messages
A consumer of this service is assumed to have the privileges to perform associations between the specified Visa Applications and Health Cases.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

The consumer must have the following before calling this service:
One or more valid Visa Application Ids
One or more valid Health Case Ids. For Health Cases to be linked, the Health Case Ids must not already be linked to any Visa Application. For Health Cases to be unlinked, the Health Case Ids must already be linked to the specified Visa Applications.

Service Composition

This service is a not composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services in the Service Portfolio. This service needs only one ICSE provider call to complete.

Service Flow

The detail of the flow is as follows:
Service Consumer invokes service with UpadateVisaApplicationAssociationsRequest input message on ESB
ESB transforms UpdateVisaApplicationAssociationsRequest into ICSE ApplicationMaintenanceRequest input message and sends it to ICSE
ICSE executes CICS transaction and returns ICSE ApplicationMaintenanceResponse output message back to ESB
ESB transforms ICSE ApplicationMaintenanceResponse output message into UpdateVisaApplicationAssociationsResponse output message
ESB returns UpdateVisaApplicationAssociationsResponse output message to Service Consumer

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service is used as a logical Enterprise Service meaning there is no need for any physical transformation of messages between consumers and providers. The Service has been setup to allow ICSE to create and modify Health Case Assessments in HAP.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is used as a logical Enterprise Service meaning there is no need for any physical transformation of messages between consumers and providers. The Service has been setup to allow ICSE to create and modify Health Case Assessments in HAP.
This Services purpose is to allow HAP to be maintained as the data is changed in ICSE and that both systems will reflect current state of the Health Assessment.

Service Behaviour

This updates HAP with the details of the Health Assessment from ICSE. HAP uses the Health Case ID supplied from ICSE to match against the existing Health Cases and either creates a new Assessment or updates an existing assessment based on the current state of HAP.
The Service sends a subset of the Health Assessment details to HAP including;
BIO Graphical Details
Health Assessment Details

Service Variants

There are no service variants.

Service Dependencies

There are no service dependencies as all IDs are supplied by the consumer.

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

  1. An event is generated by the Service Consumer or a System which invokes the ModifyHealthCaseAssessmentRequest service directly on HAP Queues.
  2. HAP retrieves the message from the HAP Queue and processes the messages.
  3. HAP returns a valid ModifyHealthCaseAssessmentReponse to the consumer.
    1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
  4. An event is generated by the Service Consumer or a System which invokes the ModifyHealthCaseAssessmentRequest service directly on HAP Queues.
  5. HAP retrieves the message from the HAP Queue and processes the messages.
  6. HAP returns a SOAP Error to the consumer.

Transformation

No transformations take place on this service. See Associated SV423 Modify Health Case Assessment Micro document.

Service State Management Decisions

Provider system errors
If provider system returns an error code at any stage of the service execution, the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer. This service will not return partial response messages.

models.description:
Service Usage

The Service publishes / Modifies the relevant Health Case Context and Health Requirements stored in the back-end systems (GCMS and HAP) to eMedical.
models.readme:
Service Usage

The Service publishes / Modifies the relevant Health Case Context and Health Requirements stored in the back-end systems (GCMS and HAP) to eMedical.
The service is initiated upon the following business triggers:
Upon a decision being made in the back end system that the client will need to complete a medical examination.

Service Behaviour
