models.description: This file is a core file and reused by multipe sevices

Service Usage

The service is used to store an information record and its associated metadata into the Record Keeping System (currently implemented via TRIM) for an indefinite period of time. When storing an information record the user has the capability to specify whether the information record can be further modified (eg functionality of Drafting Correspondence) or whether it is to be locked down as a final version.
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service is used to store an information record and its associated metadata into the Record Keeping System (currently implemented via TRIM) for an indefinite period of time. When storing an information record the user has the capability to specify whether the information record can be further modified (eg functionality of Drafting Correspondence) or whether it is to be locked down as a final version.
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a consumer wishes to store metadata and Information Record (IR)
This service allows the consumer to store/relate a single information record into multiple business context containers and multiple parties containers. The consumers provides at least one Business Context and optionally parties with the Information Record to be stored. The Information Record is physically stored only within a single Business Context Container and related to other Business Context and party containers.
An Information Record could be a single document or a correspondence with a list of attachments.

Service Behaviour

This service provides information record storage in the following steps:
The consumer provides the following metadata and Information Record inputs:
Binary Large Objects (for storing electronic copies) and related
Metadata
Metadata only if hard copy information records
Related Information Record ID and relationship type
Record Management Access Groups
Record Management Security Classification and Caveats
Business Contexts
Party Contexts
Electronic Container ID.
The service invokes Create/Search Container, Store Document and Link Document Record Keeping Services (RKS) passing the metadata and the Information Record.
RKS executes the service call and returns either:
A Record ID for the newly stored Information Record
A Record ID of the container where the Information Record is contained in.
A Paper File Created Flag for the Business Context container that the IR is contained in.
Business Context (with Business Context Container Id)
Client Sub Container Context (with Client Subcontainer Id)
OR
An Enterprise Error detailing why the service was unsuccessful.
A consumer of this service receives either:
A Record ID for the successfully stored information record
An Electronic Container ID
A paper File Created Flag
An optional list of Business Context
An optional list of Party Context
OR
An error message if an information record cannot be stored successfully for technical reasons
This service has been altered to use MTOM/XOP by changing the base64Binary fields to xsd:anyType so that a reference to the attachment can be sent. This is converted by ESB to a base64Binary attachment reference before it is sent to RKS. The developer can choose to either convert the link into a base64 or not convert and not validate.

Service Variants

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique identifier for Business Context as a Business Context Id with Business Context Type and Sub Type and a valid Electronic Container ID. This service also expects that the Meta information provided with a document will be record keeping compliant.

Service Composition

Although this service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other enterprise services within the Service Portfolio, it makes a call to SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0 in order to retrieve details available for a selected Parties in a consolidated records. These party details are used by the provider service to search and create party containers and party sub containers

Service Flow

The normal flow for this service is a call to RMS to store information record. The return message contains TRIM unique Record Id.
The following service flow describes a successful execution path.
Service Invocation and Retrieve Multiple Parties
Service Consumer invokes service SV059 on ESB with StoreInformationRecordRequest.
Use AF1 IF StoreInformationRecordRequest.InformationRecord.StoreiNformationRecord.StoreCorrespondence.PrimaryCorrespondenceItem.BodyContentRenditionList!=NULL
AND StoreInformationRecordRequest.InformationRecord.StoreiNformationRecord.StoreCorrespondence.PrimaryCorrespondenceItem.BodyContent= NULL.
IF PartyContext is provided with the service request, ESB transforms StoreInformationRecordRequest into RetrieveMultiplePartiesRequest with the Party Ids from those Party Contexts for which the PartyContext.PartySubContainerId=NULL.
ESB invokes SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0 with RetrieveMultiplePartiesRequest.
ESB receives RetrieveMultiplePartiesResponse from SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0.
Use AF2 if SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0 fails.
Store and Process the Record into Business Context Container
ESB transforms StoreInformationRecordRequest and RetrieveMultiplePartiesResponse into StoreRecordRequest.
ESB invokes RecordKeeping.storeRecord () with StoreRecordRequest.
ESB receives response StoreRecordResponse from RecordKeeping.StoreRecord ().
Use AF3 if RecordKeeping.StoreRecord () fails.
ESB transform StoreRecordResponse into StoreInformationRecordResponse.
ESB return StoreInformationRecordResponse to service consumer.
Alternate Flow 1
ESB returns message SV059.MSG-E05 to consumer.
Alternate Flow 2
If SV002.1 times out, ESB returns message SV059.MSG-E03 to consumer else ESB capture the error code and error message from SV002.1 and concatenate to body of message SV059.MSG-E01 then return to consumer
Alternate Flow 3
If StoreRecord is timeout, ESB returns message SV059.MSG-E03 to consumer else ESB capture the error code and error message from RecordKeeping.storeDocumentSet() and concatenate to body of message SV059.MSG-E01 then return to consumer.

Service State Management Decisions

No State management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

An information record represents any electronic or hardcopy item of documentation or correspondence (correspondence encompasses any associated attachments). This may include electronic mail (correspondence), case assessment documents, plans, notes, interview reports, health reports or application forms
models.readme:
Service Usage

An information record represents any electronic or hardcopy item of documentation or correspondence (correspondence encompasses any associated attachments). This may include electronic mail (correspondence), case assessment documents, plans, notes, interview reports, health reports or application forms
The service enables a consumer to select, retrieve and reserve an Information Record for modification.
In the context of the service, all information records fall into two distinct sub types, Document/Attachment and Primary Information Record Item. If the requested subtype is a Document/Attachment the service returns physical Information Record and its associated metadata. If the requested subtype is a Primary Information Record Item the service will return the Primary Information Record Item (contents) a list of associated attachment(s) and related metadata. The consumer may then choose to re-invoke the service to retrieve a specific record (attachment).

Service Behaviour

The execution of this service is a step that will allow VPO to view Information record list and then select a particular information record to view.

To invoke the service a consumer inputs:
Information Record Id ,
Checkout Requested Flag and

The Provider System responds with :
Metadata associated with content of the Information Record, or if applicable, metadata associated with associated attachments. Metadata includes the date and time the document was last updated and its edit status.
Content of the record (An electronic file of any type e.g. .txt, .doc, .pdf, .xls etc)
Business context associations(s)
Related record associations(s)
Container metadata (Id, type, location, paper file created flag if applicable)

Note: The service does not provide a complete historical audit trail of changes made to an information record. However this function is available through the existing TRIM user interface.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique information record Id. This service also expects that the meta-information provided with an information record will be record keeping compliant.

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

The normal flow for this service is a call to RKS to retrieve information record.
The following service flow describes a successful execution path.

  1. Service Consumer invokes service on ESB with
    RetrieveInformationRecordRequest.
  2. ESB transforms RetrieveInformationRequest to RetrieveRecordRequest.
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeeping.RetrieveRecordRequest() on Record Keeping interface using RetrieveRecordRequest object.
  4. Record Keeping service returns RetrieveRecordResponse to ESB.
  5. Use Alternate flow 1 if Record keeping service raises Error
  6. ESB transforms RetrieveRecordResponse to RetrieveInformationResponse and returns response to the consumer.

1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1
ESB transforms errors into enterprise error message and returns to the consumer. Please see the section Service Enterprise Return Code Message for more details.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service allows the service consumer to update metadata and the body binary associated with an Information Record. Information record in this context represents any item of documentation that is required to be kept as a record for any given length of time. Examples of an Information Record include but are not limited to:
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service allows the service consumer to update metadata and the body binary associated with an Information Record. Information record in this context represents any item of documentation that is required to be kept as a record for any given length of time. Examples of an Information Record include but are not limited to:
Case assessment, plan or notes
Interview report
Health report
Application form
Primary Correspondence
Information Record will have two main parts:
Metadata associated with the content of the record
The content of the record
Metadata will contain compliance elements (required by National Archives of Australia NAA standards) and context specific elements required by the consumer (eg. data used for searching).
Actual content of the record can be a Body Binary of any type (eg. txt, PDF, doc, xsl, jpg, bmp ).
The service also allows the service consumer to register a Hardcopy correspondence or document to the Record Keeping System.
The execution of this service is a step that will occur when:
The Visa Processing Officer returns original document(s) to client. This is not considered a new outbound correspondence but additional information for existing correspondence.
The Visa Processing Officer changes the status of the correspondence (for example from unactioned to no action required).
The Visa Processing Officer checks in a new version of the Binary File to replace the old version.
The Visa Processing Officer registers a Hardcopy Correspondence or document to the Record Keeping System

Service Behaviour

A consumer of this service provides:
Identity of the Information Record
Any data item which is to be modified by the consumer. This encompasses data from any of the following CDM Entities:
Information Record Status
Correspondence Item
Document
Related Information Records
Body Binary Content
A consumer of this service receives either:
An Enterprise Service Acknowledgement
Or
An Enterprise Error detailing why the retrieve was unsuccessful.
This service also provides the following behaviour:
The service behaviour in modifying security caveat of an Information Record is by Adding new Security Caveat to the record in addition to the existing caveat. In other words, the service will not replace or modify existing Caveats in a record
The service behaviour in modifying Access Group of an Information Record is by Granting new Access to new set of users but not revoking access from existing users.
Follows an all or nothing principal for updates. This means if any particular part of the update is unable to be performed, then nothing will be updated and the service will return an Enterprise error.
The service uses MTOM/XOP instead of SOAP with Attachments (SwA). If an endpoint requires SwA then a converter will be used after the message is delivered by ESB.
This service has been altered to use MTOM/XOP by changing the base64Binary fields to xsd:anyType so that a reference to the attachment can be sent. This is converted by ESB to a base64Binary attachment reference before it is sent to RKS. The developer can choose to either convert the link into a base64 or not convert and not validate.

Service Dependencies

This service consumer must have previously acquired a valid Correspondence Item Id or Information Record Id.

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service. i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio

Service Flow

Service Consumer invokes service on ESB with ModifyInformationRequest.
ESB invokes RecordKeeping.ModifyRecord() on Record Keeping interface using ModifyRecordRequest object.
Record Keeping service returns ModifyRecordResponse to ESB.
Use AF1 if ModifyRecordResponse returns with error or timeout
ESB transforms ModifyRecordResponse to ModifyInformationRecordResponse and returns response to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return SV201.MSG-E03 to the consumer.
ESB returns message SV201.MSG-E01 to consumer.

models.readme:
Service Usage

This service allows the consumer to retrieve a summary list of all information records in provider system matching the specified search criteria. The summary list retrieved will represent the current status of the specified information records.

Service Behaviour

To invoke the service a consumer inputs one or more of the following attributes. If more than one of the following attributes is specified, the input rationale will be logically and together (to enable a more accurate and focused search):
Party Id
Business Context Id / Type/Subtype
Information Record Current Status
(Correspondence) Subject Text
(Correspondence) Sender Details
(Correspondence) Recipient Details
(Correspondence) Sent date/time filter
(Correspondence) Received date/time filter
(Correspondence) Direction Type/Channel Type
(Correspondence) Work Centre Category Name
Case Management: Case Activity Id
(Correspondence) Hardcopy flag
Document Type
BussinessContextContainerId
BussinessContext Details
The Provider System responds with a summary list of information records. The following attributes are provided for each information record on the summary list:
Information Record Item Id
(Correspondence) Sender Details
(Correspondence) Recipient Details
(Correspondence) Subject Text
(Correspondence) Direction Type/Channel Type
(Correspondence) Received Date
(Correspondence) Sent Date
Information Record Status
Document Details (File name/ File Extension/ Size)
Information Record Title
Has Attachments Flag
Edit Status
Security Classification/Security Caveat Type
Hardcopy flag
Case Activity Id
BussinessContextContainerId
BussinessContext Details
ResultSetResponse

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

The normal flow for this service is a call to Provider (RKS) to search information record.
The detail of the flow is as follows:
Consumer invokes SearchInformationRecord on ESB
ESB transforms SearchInformationRecordRequest to searchRecordRequest
ESB invokes RecordKeepingService.searchRecord() on RecordKeeping component using searchRecordRequest
Use Alternate Flow 1 if RecordKeepingService.searchRecord() returns error.
For each element present in searchRecordRequest the RecordKeeping component will form up the appropriate RecordSearch clauses and use them to perform a Search operation against the TRIM database
For each record matching the input searching criteria the Record Keeping component will create a SearchRecord instance and add it to the RecordKeepingService.searchRecordResponse.
The Record Keeping component returns searchRecordResponse to the ESB
The ESB transforms searchRecordResponse to SearchInformationRecordResponse
The ESB returns SearchInformationRecordResponse to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 1
ESB transforms errors into enterprise error message and returns to the consumer. Please see the section Service Enterprise Return Code Message for more details.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

Service Usage

This service is used to create a correspondence item from an identified correspondence template, and convert it into a format such as pdf or html, ready for delivery via a specific channel (email, post, or fax).
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service is used to create a correspondence item from an identified correspondence template, and convert it into a format such as pdf or html, ready for delivery via a specific channel (email, post, or fax).
This service is used for automatically generated correspondence that does not require a manual review step before formatting (e.g. a grant approval letter for an auto-granted visa application).

Service Behaviour

This service generates and formats correspondence in the following steps:
Batch Configuration Id
Template data, a flexible content element, which may include:
Channel Type
Recipient details
Details of the primary Party whom the correspondence concerns (may be the same as recipient)
Details of the Departmental Officer sending the correspondence
Business Context Details (eg. Compliance Case, Visa grant, Request for further information, etc).
This service calls Thunderhead directly to create an item of correspondence and format it for a specific delivery channel.
A consumer of this service receives either:
A Channel Formatted Correspondence Item,
Or
An Enterprise error message.

Service Dependencies

This service consumer must have previously acquired a valid Batch Configuration Id via a previous invocation of another service. It also assumes that the consumer uses the correct template data for Thunderhead.

Service Composition

This service does not require any composition. It calls Thunderhead directly using the Template Id and the Template Data and receives a finalised correspondence.

Service Flow

The normal flow for this service is a call to Provider (Thunderhead) to format a correspondence item passed in as template data nd return it in formatted channel type to the consumer.
The following service flow describes a successful execution path.
Service Consumer invokes service SV261 on ESB with CreateAndFormatCorrespondenceRequest
ESB invokes the operation JobAPIWebWrapped.executePreview on the provider (Thunderhead) SOAP/HTTP WebService and transforms CreateAndFormatCorrespondenceRequest to JobAPIWebWrapped.executePreviewRequest
Set BodyContent on the Thunderhead message
ESB receives a response
Use AF1, if invocation failed.
ESB transforms JobAPIWebWrapped.executePreviewResponse into CreateAndFormatCorrespondenceResponse.
ESB returns FormatCorrespondenceResponse to service consumer.
executePreviewResponse returned from the Thunderhead contains a body and 0 or more attachments based on the channel type:
Body Content is returned in the Thunderhead master channel. Although the Thunderhead schema allows for multiple master channels, only one master channel will ever be returned. The encoding for the body content depends on the channel type:
For channel type of Email, body content is HTML encoded
For channel type of Fax or Post, body content is PDF encoded
Attachments may be returned for all channel types. Attachments are returned in the Thunderhead slave channels. The encoding for each attachment is always PDF format, irrespective of channel type. The attachment name is also returned with each attachment. The following xml fragment from the Thunderhead response gives an example of how attachment names are returned:
AttachmentName

Form 1282- Australian Values Statement

These elements already occur in each of the slave channels that are currently received; the only difference is that they will be populated with child elements. The first contains the property name, in this case "AttachmentName", and the second contains the property value, which is the attachment name.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
If the service call to Thunderhead is timeout, ESB should return SV261.MSG-E02 to the consumer.
If Thunderhead returns a SOAP fault, ESB should transform the SOAP fault from Thunderhead Server into SV261.MSG-E01 and return to consumer. The body of the SOAP fault from Thunderhead will pass on to the consumer without modification.
ESB should log the error message before returning the response to the consumer.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

Service Usage

The service is used to lodge visa application information captured through online channels into a visa processing system.
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service is used to lodge visa application information captured through online channels into a visa processing system.

The LodgeSkilledApplication variant enables lodgement of the following Application Forms:

  • SRV-AP-491 - Application for a Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) visa
  • SRV-AP-494 - Application for a Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional (Provisional) visa
  • SRV-NOM-494 - Nomination for a Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional (Provisional) Visa

SVS656 is a reimplementation of the existing SV472 RegisterVisaApplication service, split into multiple variants for the various Visa streams:

The proposed list of variants includes:

  • Skilled (this schema)
  • Protection/Humanitarian
  • Visitor
  • Working Holiday
  • Student
  • Family

For more background on this new service see the discussion paper ADD2019/560143.

Service Behavior

Upon successful submission this service sends an acknowledgment.
As of the NOV19 release, an asynchronous SV472 RegisterVisaApplicationResponse is returned.

Transformation

Request Transformation:

The SV656 Request message is transformed into an ICSE eCommerce provider message.

Response Transformation:

The ICSE eCommerce provider message is transformed into a SV472 Response message as noted above.

Service Usage

SV500 Notify Account Holder Update notifies departmental systems of changes to external user details (eg. name, email address, etc).

Service Behaviour

ESS publishes a SV500 message when a users details have changed. Subscribing systems will receive the SV500 message and if the message relates to a user stored within specific system, will perform updates to data held within that system.

Service Flow

A normal flow for this service is for ESS to publish a SV500 message when user details have changed. Subscribing systems will receive the SV500 message and if the message relates to a user stored within the specific system, will perform updates to data held within that system.

Transformation

N/A

eVisa/ePLUS will the payment status to determine whether the client can continue to editing the transaction or not

models.description:
Service Usage

OS001 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application.
models.readme:
Service Usage

OS001 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application.
The search is conducted using a Citizenship Certificate Number, with further filtering by Biographic Criteria (Date of Birth, Family Name and Given Name).

The service orchestrates calls to services 'SV341' and 'IN009' to retrieve biographic data associated with the matching party's business dealing, and to ISR via SV150 to retrieve an associated image.

Service Behaviour

The service will attempt to retrieve data for a single party based on the supplied criteria, according to the following flow and business rules:
Citizenship
OS001.1 The Citizenship Certificate Number ('CCN') is applied to find matching candidate parties:
Matching rules:

  • 'CCN' = PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFER.IDENTIFIERVALUE where IDENTIFIERCODE_TYPE = 'CID'
    OR
  • 'CCN' = DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTNUMBER where DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTTYPE in ('certificateofevidenceofcitizenship', 'citizenship_certificate')

OS001.2 If no parties match 'CCN', a response is returned with the message PRTY00091.
OS001.3 If one or more parties match 'CCN', the Biographic criteria is matched against the ICSE Principal Preferred name of the candidate(s):
Matching rules:

For PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE = 'CID' AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGE_TYPE = '1'

  • 'Date of Birth Year' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEYEAR
  • 'Date of Birth Month' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH (if 'Date of Birth Month' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH in (0,-1))
  • 'Date of Birth Day' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY (if 'Date of Birth Day' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY in (0,-1))
  • 'Family Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.FAMILY_NAME
  • 'Given Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME (If 'Given Name' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME = '')

OS001.4 If no parties match (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response is returned with the message PRTY00092.
OS001.5 If multiple parties match (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response is returned with the message PRTY00093.
OS001.6 Where a single party is matched after applying (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response will be sent as follows:
Response: Biographic Data
OS001.7 If IncludeBiographicFlag = 'T', Biographic Data will be returned as follows:
Return Biographic details where PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGE_TYPE = '1'
Set NameUsageType = 'Principal Preferred'.

OS001.7.1 If AliasNameFlag = 'T'
Also return Biographic details where
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2' OR PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2')

Set NameUsageType = 'Alias' for all names returned as a result of AliasNameFlag = 'T'.

OS001.7.2 If AliasExistsFlag = 'T'
Also return AliasExistsFlag.
Set = 'T' where exists (
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2' OR PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2')
)
Else Set 'F'

Response: Other Data
OS001.8 Deceased Indicator:
Set 'T' where exists DEATH.EFFECTIVETOTIMESTAMP IS NULL.
ELSE Set 'F'

OS001.9 Citizenship Status:
If exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '5' SET = 'Acquired' ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '9' SET = 'Loss'
ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLE_STATUS = '3' SET = 'Approved not Acquired'
Else SET = 'Not Approved'.

OS001.10 Document Status:
For CCN that matched:
If exists DOCUMENTEVENT.DOCUMENTEVENTTYPE = 'VOIDEDREASON' SET = 'Void'.
Else SET = 'Current'

Response: Image
If IncludeImage = 'T' the OS service will attempt to retrieve the latest Citizenship Image from ISR via SV150, where it is lawful to disclose:
Retrieve Rules:
Call SV150 with the image id of the latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where
BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT = 'Citizenship' and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest')
And localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) >= '2009-09-17' And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCETYPE = 'FC'
If no such image id exists
Call SV150 with the image id of the latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where
BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT= 'Citizenship' and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT NOT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest')
And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE_TYPE = 'FC'

OS001.11 If no Image exists. Return message PRTY00095
OS001.12 If Image exists but not lawful to return. Return message PRTY00096.
OS001.13 If Image exists but ISR cannot find image. Return message PRTY00097
OS001.14 If Image Retrieve is successful, return message PRTY00094.
OS001.15 If IncludeImage = 'F', return message PRTY00094.
OS001.16 IsImageAvailable (FaciaImageCount):
If image exists set = 'T' Else 'F'

Service Usage

OS002 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application, and to conduct a Biometric verification using the provided Image.
models.readme:
Service Usage

OS002 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application, and to conduct a Biometric verification using the provided Image.
The search is conducted using a Citizenship Certificate Number, with further filtering by Biographic Criteria (Date of Birth, Family Name and Given Name).
A Biometric verification is conducted using the provided Image and the Biometric data retrieved for a party.

The service orchestrates calls to services 'SV341' and 'IN009' to retrieve biographic data associated with the matching party's business dealing, and to BMS via SV606 to conduct the Biometric verification.

Service Behaviour

The service will attempt to retrieve data for a single party based on the supplied criteria, according to the following flow and business rules:
Citizenship
OS002.1 The Citizenship Certificate Number ('CCN') is applied to find matching candidate parties:
Matching rules:

  • 'CCN' = PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFER.IDENTIFIERVALUE where IDENTIFIERCODE_TYPE = 'CID'
    OR
  • 'CCN' = DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTNUMBER where DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTTYPE in ('certificateofevidenceofcitizenship', 'citizenship_certificate')

OS002.2 If no parties match 'CCN', a response is returned with the message PRTY00091.
OS002.3 If one or more parties match 'CCN', the Biographic criteria is matched against the ICSE Principal Preferred name of the candidate(s):
Matching rules:

For PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE = 'CID' AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGE_TYPE = '1'

  • 'Date of Birth Year' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEYEAR
  • 'Date of Birth Month' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH (if 'Date of Birth Month' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH in (0,-1))
  • 'Date of Birth Day' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY (if 'Date of Birth Day' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY in (0,-1))
  • 'Family Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.FAMILY_NAME
  • 'Given Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME (If 'Given Name' nor provide match BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME = '')

OS002.4 If no parties match (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response is returned with the message PRTY00092.
OS002.5 If multiple parties match (CCN + Biographic criteria), a response is returned with the message PRTY00093.

OS002.6 Where a single party is matched after applying (CCN + Biographic criteria) the OS service will attempt a Biometric Verification via SV606. A response will be sent as follows:
Response: Biometric Match Result
Biometric Match Rules:
Call SV606 with the PROBE Image and BAMSID of the latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT = 'Citizenship'
and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCETYPE = 'FC'
If no such image id exists
Call SV606 with the PROBE Image and BAMSID of the latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT= 'Citizenship' and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT NOT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCETYPE = 'FC'

If IncludeImage = 'F' OR BAMSID sent is for BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) < '2009-09-17' SET SV606 IncludeImage flag = 'F'

NB Biometric Match Result is still returned even if it is not 'lawful to disclose' image.

OS002.7 If SV606 call fails due to Probe Image not being of Biometric Quality, return message PRTY00100.
OS002.8 If Biometric Match Result = 'No Match', return message PRTY00099.

Response: Biographic Data
OS002.9 If IncludeBiographicFlag = 'T' and Biometric Match Result = 'Match', Biographic Data will be returned as follows:
Return Biographic details where PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGE_TYPE = '1'
Set NameUsageType = 'Principal Preferred'.

OS002.9.1 If AliasNameFlag = 'T'
Also return Biographic details where
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2' OR PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2')

Set NameUsageType = 'Alias' for all names returned as a result of AliasNameFlag = 'T'.

OS002.9.2 If AliasExistsFlag = 'T'
Also return AliasExistsFlag.
Set = 'T' where exists (
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2' OR PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2')
)
Else Set 'F'

Response: Other Data - Only return where Biometric Match Result = 'Match'
OS002.10 Deceased Indicator:
Set 'T' where exists DEATH.EFFECTIVETOTIMESTAMP IS NULL.
ELSE Set 'F'

OS002.11 Citizenship Status:
If exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '5' SET = 'Acquired' ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '9' SET = 'Loss'
ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLE_STATUS = '3' SET = 'Approved not Acquired'
Else SET = 'Not Approved'.

OS002.12 Document Status:
For CCN that matched:
If exists DOCUMENTEVENT.DOCUMENTEVENTTYPE = 'VOIDEDREASON' SET = 'Void'.
Else SET = 'Current'

Response: Image
If IncludeImage = 'T' and Biometric Match Result = 'Match' and Image is 'lawful to disclose', return the Image against which the PROBE Image was verified.
NB Citizenship Images other than ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') prior to 17/09/2009 are lawful to disclose. This is checked before setting IncludeImage flag in SV606 call.

OS002.13 If no Image exists. Return message PRTY00095
OS002.14 If Image exists but not lawful to return. Return message PRTY00096.
OS002.15 If Image exists but BMS cannot find image. Return message PRTY00097
OS002.16 If Biometric Match Result = 'Match', return message PRTY00094.
OS002.17 IsImageAvailable (FaciaImageCount):
If image exists set = 'T' Else 'F'

models.readme:
Service Usage

OS002 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Visa details, and to conduct a Biometric verification using the provided Image.
The search is conducted using a Visa Grant Number or Document number, with further filtering by Biographic Criteria (Date of Birth, Family Name and Given Name).
A Biometric verification is conducted using the provided Image and the Biometric data retrieved for a party.

The service orchestrates calls to services 'SV341' and 'IN009' to retrieve biographic data associated with the matching party's business dealing, and to BMS via SV606 to conduct the Biometric verification.

models.description:
Service Usage

OS003 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application, and to conduct a Biometric verification using the provided Image.
models.readme:
Service Usage

OS003 is an Orchestration Service that provides the ability to search and retrieve Biographic and Biometric data associated with a client's Citizenship application, and to conduct a Biometric verification using the provided Image.
The search is conducted using Biographic Criteria (Date of Birth, Family Name and Given Name).
A Biometric verification is conducted using the provided Image and the Biometric data retrieved for one or more matching parties.
The service orchestrates calls to service IN009 to retrieve biographic data associated with the matching party's business dealing, and to BMS via SV606 to conduct the Biometric verification.

Service Behaviour

The service will attempt to retrieve data for a single party based on the supplied criteria, according to the following flow and business rules:
Citizenship BUSINESSCONTEXT = 'CITIZENSHIP' OS003.1 The Biographic criteria is matched against ICSE Principal Preferred biographic data, for parties with Citizenship Applications: Matching rules: For PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE = 'CID' AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '1'

  • 'Date of Birth Year' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEYEAR
  • 'Date of Birth Month' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH (if 'Date of Birth Month' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEMONTH in (0,-1))
  • 'Date of Birth Day' = BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY (if 'Date of Birth Day' not provided match BIOGRAPHIC.BIRTHDATEDAY in (0,-1))
  • 'Family Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.FAMILY_NAME
  • 'Given Name' = BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME (If 'Given Name' nor provide match BIOGRAPHIC.GIVENNAME = '')
    AND Exists Citizenship Application
    OS003.2 If no parties match Biographic criteria, a response is returned with the message PRTY00092.
    OS003.3 If more than 10 parties match Biographic criteria, a response is returned with the message PRTY00093.
    OS003.4 Where between 1 and 10 parties match Biographic criteria, the OS service will attempt a Biometric Verification via SV606. A response will be sent with as follows:
    Response: Biometric Match Result
    Biometric Match Rules:
    Call SV606 with the PROBE Image and FOR EACH CANDIDATE (1-10) the BAMSID as per the following rules: The latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT = 'Citizenship'
    and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCETYPE = 'FC'
    If no such image id exists for a candidate
    The latest (based on localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) BIOMETRICENROLMENT where
    BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSCONTEXTTEXT= 'Citizenship' and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT NOT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest')
    And BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE. BIOMETRICIMAGEREFERENCE_TYPE = 'FC'

If IncludeImage = 'F' OR ALL BAMSID sent are for BIOMETRICENROLMENT.BUSINESSEVENTTEXT IN ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') and BIOMETRICENROLMENT.localfacialacquisitiontimestamp) < '2009-09-17' SET SV606 IncludeImage flag = 'F'

NB Biometric Match Result is still returned even if it is not 'lawful to disclose' image.

OS003.5 If SV606 call fails due to Probe Image not being of Biometric Quality, return message PRTY00100.
OS003.6 If Biometric Match Result = 'No Match', return message PRTY00099.
Response: Biographic Data
OS003.7 If IncludeBiographicFlag = 'T' and Biometric Match Result = 'Match', Biographic Data will be returned as follows:
Return Biographic details where PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '1' Set NameUsageType = 'Principal Preferred'. OS003.7.1 If AliasNameFlag = 'T' Also return Biographic details where PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2'
OR
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2') Set NameUsageType = 'Alias' for all names returned as a result of AliasNameFlag = 'T'. OS003.7.2 If AliasExistsFlag = 'T' Also return AliasExistsFlag. Set = 'T' where exists ( PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE = '2'
OR
PARTYSYSTEMIDENTIFIER.IDENTIFIERCODETYPE not in ('CID') AND PARTYBIOGRAPHIC.NAMEUSAGETYPE in ('1', '2') ) Else Set 'F' Response: Other Data - Only return where Biometric Match Result = 'Match' OS003.8 Deceased Indicator: Set 'T' where exists DEATH.EFFECTIVETO_TIMESTAMP IS NULL.
ELSE Set 'F'

OS003.9 Citizenship Status:
If exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '5' SET = 'Acquired' ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '9' SET = 'Loss'
ElseIf exists CITIZENSHIP where BUSINESSSERVICEROLE.ROLESTATUS = '3' SET = 'Approved not Acquired' Else SET = 'Not Approved'. OS003.10 Document Status: If exists DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTTYPE = citizenshipcertificate' AND EXISTS 'DOCUMENTEVENT.DOCUMENTEVENTTYPE = 'VOIDEDREASON' SET = 'Void'. Elseif exists DOCUMENT.DOCUMENTTYPE = citizenship_certificate' SET = 'Current'
Else SET = 'Not Applicable'

Response: Image
If IncludeImage = 'T' and Biometric Match Result = 'Match' and Image is 'lawful to disclose', return the Image against which the PROBE Image was compared.
NB Citizenship Images other than ('Citizenshipinterview','CitizenshipTest') prior to 17/09/2009 are lawful to disclose.
OS003.11 If no Image exists. Return message PRTY00095.
NB In the case of multiple candidates, this message will only apply if no candidate parties have an image.
OS003.12 If Image exists but not lawful to return. Return message PRTY00096.
NB In the case of multiple candidates, this check only applies to the image for the party the subject of a Biometric Match Result of 'Match'
OS003.13 If Image exists but BMS cannot find image. Return message PRTY00097
NB In the case of multiple candidates, this message will only apply if BMS cannot find an image for any of the candidates.
OS003.14 If Biometric Match Result = 'Match', return message PRTY00094.
OS003.15 IsImageAvailable (FaciaImageCount):
If Image exists set = 'T' Else 'F'

models.description:
Service Usage

This service is used to Retrieve Biometric By Visa's

Service Usage

The service is used by consumers to find a Party (Person or Organisation) using specific search criteria such as biographic data, identity documents or any associated role the Party may have (e.g. Registered Migration Agent, Non Registered Overseas Migration Agent, etc).
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service is used by consumers to find a Party (Person or Organisation) using specific search criteria such as biographic data, identity documents or any associated role the Party may have (e.g. Registered Migration Agent, Non Registered Overseas Migration Agent, etc).
The execution of this service is a step that may occur naturally in any business process where the goal of the user is to locate a Party. If the Party cannot be found, the user may have to refine their search criteria values.
The service returns a list of Party summary information that matches the search criteria. There is sufficient data in the Party summary to allow a user to determine if this is likely to be the Party of interest and whether or not to invoke another service to retrieve full Party details.

Service Behaviour

This service provides Party Search functionality in the following steps:
The consumer invokes the service with following elements as part of SearchPartyRequest message.
Party Search Type
Inquiry Level
Party Role
And either one of the following
Person Details
Organization Detail
Party Identifier.
The consumer receives either
A list of Party Summaries for matched active Party records. The data retrieved is constrained to the level of visibility for the security profile of the user associated with the execution.
or
Enterprise error message if the search fails.
This service also provides the following behaviours:
Role Based Searching
The service supports the use of role based searching for each Party type; this has been implemented to allow searching for Parties based on a specific role they have with DIAC (e.g. Migration Agent, Non Registered Migration Agent, etc), with an optional criteria of specifying the agency associated with the role.
Followings are the list of valid role types:
Registered Migration Agent
Education Agent
Travel Agent
Non Registered Overseas Migration Agent
BAMS - Biometric Acquisition and Matching System
VLN Visa Lodgement Number
These types can be searched either individually or in combination with other types; valid Combinations are:
All Agent Types
Registered Migration Agents AND Non Registered Overseas Migration Agents
Name Token Swap
The service provides functionality to perform a name token swap for searches using Person Name biographical criteria. Specifying a name token swap requests that the provider checks if there is another more likely way for the provided name attributes to be ordered (e.g. Smith John is more likely to be John Smith).
If there is a more likely order of the name than the one provided, this alternative order will be returned within two additional response fields: OtherLastName and OtherGivenName.
Note: The search based on the original name order will still occur when a name token swap has been specified; a search is not performed on the alternative order without the user initiating it.
Advanced Searching
Advanced searching uses the GNR (Global Name Recognition) search method, which allows for fuzzy searching and requires less specific input data to return valid results (e.g. John will be matched to Jon, Jonathan and Johan). This behaviour allows consumer to search for parties, when agent roles are not specified.
For additional information on searching options refer to the CDH options paper titled Design Options Paper - Person Search.DOC
Identifier Search
The following Identifier searches are supported:
ABN
ACN
APPROVEDPDP ARBN ASX BAMSID
BOATNAME BORDERREFERRALID BOXFILENUMBER CAS CCCN CCMDSAPPOINTMENTID CCMDSJOBID CCMDSREFERRALID CCMDSSERVICEID CEN CENTREID
CERTIFICATENUMBER CID CITIZENSHIPAPPOINTMENTID CLASSACTIONNAME CLIENTCASEID CRIMINALDEPORTID ELMAEXAMINEEID FILENUMBER
HATSCLIENTID
IOMID IRISCLIENTID MARN MPMS NIC OCN OFFSHOREBOATTASKFORCEID
PERMISSIONREQUESTNUMBER
PID
PVBOATANDSQUENCEID
PVBOATTASKFORCENUMBER PVCASEID RECEIPTNUMBER
REFUGEEID RESICASEID REVENUERECEIPTINGID SAFEHAVENGROUPNAME
SCID
SECURITYREFERRALID
SPECIALNEEDSGROUPTYPE SRI SSC STEPSORGANISATIONID TRN UNHCRID
VISAAPPLICATIONID
VISAEVIDENCENUMBER
VISAGRANTNUMBER
VLN
VRTSI
SPONSORSHIPAGREEMENTNUMBER
BUSINESSCONTEXTCONTAINERNUMBER IRISVISAAPPLICATIONID

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

Depending on the search type and search criteria being used, this service will access either the ICSE or CDH provider systems. The general breakdown is as follows:
Search Type Provider
Person or Organisation or Id (Without an Agent Role specified) CDH Search
Person & Organisation (With an Agent Role specified) ICSE Search
Identity Document ICSE Search
For Person and Organisation (without an Agent Role specified):
The Party Summary data is returned by CDH.
The ESB:
Where necessary, transforms SearchPartyRequest to CDH.searchParty with Person or Organisation as appropriate.
Invokes searchParty.
If no results then generate warning message (SV001.MSG-W01) and END flow.
If one or more results are returned they will be in searchPartyResponse format.
ESB returns searchPartyResponse to consumer.
For Person and Organisation (with an Agent Role specified):
Service Consumer invokes the service on the ESB with SearchPartyRequest.
ESB will recognise as an ICSE-Search based on the presence of an Agent Role value in the PartyRoleType attribute/s.
For ICSE-Search, ESB invokes the secondary provider ICSE as follows:
ESB extracts the GivenName, FamilyName, PartyRoleType (multiple values can be submitted), PartyRoleId and related OrganisationName from the searchParty.RequestObject and transforms to ICSE.SearchAgentRequest
ESB invokes ICSE.SearchAgentRequest.
ESB transforms the ICSE.SearchAgentResponse to SearchPartyResponse.
If no search results found then return SV001.MSG-W01 and END flow.
ESB returns SearchPartyResponse to consumer.
Note: A warning will be returned where one type of Party is expected but a record of another Party type is found with the provided search criteria. SV001.MSG-W05 is returned when the search criteria match an Organization, but a Person was expected. SV001.MSG-W04 is returned when the search criteria match an Organization, but a Person was expected.
Limitations: If a name search yields more than 1,000 Parties, only 1,000 Parties are returned with a warning PRTY0020. This limitation is not present on searches using address.

Refer to the NameHunter documentation for details of the limitations it imposes upon this service.
For Person_ID and OrganisationID search where Alternate Identifier or Role Identifier is of Type specified in section ICSE Service Provider:
Service Consumer invokes the service on the ESB with SearchPartyRequest.
ESB will recognise as an ICSE-Search based on the presence of specific Alternate Identifier or Role Identifier.
ESB invokes ICSE.SearchAgentRequest.
ESB transforms the ICSE.SearchAgentResponse to SearchPartyResponse.
For Party Search Type Identity Document and document type code of 1 (Passport):
Service Consumer invokes the service on the ESB with SearchPartyRequest.
ESB will recognise as an ICSE-Search based on the Party Search Type of Identity Document (Passport).
ESB invokes ICSE.SearchAgentRequest.
ESB transforms the ICSE.SearchAgentResponse to SearchPartyResponse.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

Modifying a Party is a step that occurs in the course of a variety of business processes where data about a Party (sometimes called a client) is required to be changed or added to in order for business processes to function correctly.
models.readme:
Service Usage

Modifying a Party is a step that occurs in the course of a variety of business processes where data about a Party (sometimes called a client) is required to be changed or added to in order for business processes to function correctly.
The typical case is where SV003 Create Party (or some other mechanism, such as the user interface of one of the provider systems) has been used at some prior time to create a Party with the data required at that time. SV004 Modify Party may be used immediately to complete the initial party record or at some time later due to an error, a change in circumstances or a new business context.
Such updates may be required for a number of business reasons, including:
For addresses
adds new addresses - for location and electronic addresses
modifies existing locations
modifies address usage
For names
Correction of wrongly entered name
Addition of an name alias, or terminates existing alias
The number of added or changed attributes can be quite varied depending on the circumstances of the change.
In SFP7 the service interface changed to incorporate following elements :
EthinicityList and MaritalStatusList
Inclusion of Ethnicity List allows the request to provide a collection of Ethnicity Type with its Start Date and End Date.
Inclusion of Marital Status List allows the request to provide a collection of Marital Status Type and its Start Date and End Date.

Service Behaviour

This service provides Party Search functionality in the following steps:
The consumer invokes the service with following elements as part of SearchPartyRequest message.
Party Search Type
Inquiry Level
Party Role
And either one of the following
Person Details
Organization Detail
Party Identifier.
The consumer receives either
A list of Party Summaries for matched active Party records. The data retrieved is constrained to the level of visibility for the security profile of the user associated with the execution.
or
Enterprise error message if the search fails.
This service also provides the following behaviours:
Role Based Searching
The service supports the use of role based searching for each Party type; this has been implemented to allow searching for Parties based on a specific role they have with DIAC (e.g. Migration Agent, Non Registered Migration Agent, etc), with an optional criteria of specifying the agency associated with the role.
Followings are the list of valid role types:
Registered Migration Agent
Education Agent
Travel Agent
Non Registered Overseas Migration Agent
BAMS - Biometric Acquisition and Matching System
VLN Visa Lodgement Number
These types can be searched either individually or in combination with other types; valid Combinations are:
All Agent Types
Registered Migration Agents AND Non Registered Overseas Migration Agents
Name Token Swap
The service provides functionality to perform a name token swap for searches using Person Name biographical criteria. Specifying a name token swap requests that the provider checks if there is another more likely way for the provided name attributes to be ordered (e.g. Smith John is more likely to be John Smith).
If there is a more likely order of the name than the one provided, this alternative order will be returned within two additional response fields: OtherLastName and OtherGivenName.
Note: The search based on the original name order will still occur when a name token swap has been specified; a search is not performed on the alternative order without the user initiating it.
Advanced Searching
The service updates the supplied attributes of the identified Party in the primary provider system, which indirectly may also update attributes in other systems via existing interfaces.
The service handles data within discrete groupings:
Biographic - a persons name, date of birth, gender, birth country code; includes name usage and source of biographic information
Identifiers system IDs and external identifiers
Contacts name details (ICSE requires that the Family Name is mandatory, although it is an optional element within the schema), addresses, phone, fax and email details; includes source of contact name details. Note that the ICSE key for address, telephone, fax and email can be specified within the request message via the SystemId and SequenceNumber.
Personal Factors such as religion, language, country of residence, name ethnicity and marital status. It uses code lookup tables while transforming the request message.
Business Context case details, detention details and UHM details
The consumer may choose to include some or all of these data groups in the same request message.
In some cases the service may create the Party in a provider system if it does not exist there already and a request message containing only a Party ID may cause this to happen.
The service does not monitor nor enforce some aspects of its usage, for example that a duplicate party is not created. It is trusted that the service consumer applications or the service provider systems enforce these constraints.
Only person Parties can be modified, but later versions of the service may also support:
Organisation parties
Party of Interest details
Prior to the SV004 request individual attributes may be null (so data is being added), or may hold values (so data is being updated). In the case of an update, the value may be being corrected, replaced, or added to. SV004 requests may include added data, updated data, or a combination of both. In most cases prior data is maintained in the provider systems rather than deleted or overwritten.
The subset of data included in the SV004 request is as determined by the service consumer within its own business context. There is no minimum data requirement for this service, and indeed a null request that does not update any data is valid. However:
A Party Id must be provided
Individual data attributes will not be carried forward from previous versions of a given data entity. Hence, individual data entities must be complete, containing all attributes not just the changed ones
Rules for individual data entities may prohibit incomplete or inconsistent attribute values
Hence, SV004 provides a flexible container by which the service consumer can provide those values that it wishes to modify.
The service returns the PartyId. It also returns other party identifiers in other provider systems if a party was created in them as part of the service processing. The Party may be modified in one or more downstream provider systems, but this update may not occur immediately in these systems.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

The flow for the Modify Party service is as follows:
The consumer constructs a ModifyPartyRequest message, including the Party ID and party data to be added or modified, and invokes SV004. Note that when SV004 is called immediately after receiving the SV003 response, the consumer must include in the SV004 request all identities that were sent in SV003, including the BiodataInformationSource against each identity. This is required because SV003 response does not return the BiodataInformationSource (since CDH does not store it), but ICSE requires it to create a client (also see step 6).
ESB calls SV002 to obtain the data held about the Party (it is expected that the party will always exist in CDH)
ESB receives the SV002 RetrievePartyResponse message and inspects it to see if it contains a CID. If the reply contains a CID, then processing continues at step 9. If no CID was returned (and so it is assumed that there is no client record in ICSE) then processing continues at step 4
The ESB determines if one of the names returned from CDH is of type Principal / Preferred. If at least one name is of type Principal / Preferred then processing coninues at step 6. If no name returned from CDH is of type Principal / Preferred then processing continues at step 5
This step is required when creating a client in ICSE to ensure that a name of type Principal / Preferred is supplied (ICSE will return an error when creating a client if a name of type Principal / Preferred is not supplied). Note: It is assumed that the consumer of this service provides a name of type Principal / Preferred. The ESB takes the identity associated with the name of type Principal / Preferred provided by the consumer and compares it against the identities returned from the previous call to SV002. If a match is found, then the name type returned by SV002 is updated to Principal / Preferred. If no match is found then the identity associated with the name of type Principal / Preferred that is provided by the consumer is added to the list of identities returned from SV002. The following identity attributes must be the same in both the SV002 RetrievePartyResponse message and the SV004 ModifyPartyRequest message for an identity to be considered matched:
FamilyName
GivenName
BirthDate (BirthDateDay, BirthDateMonth, BirthDateYear)
SexType
BirthCountryCode
NameTitleText
This step is required to ensure that each identity passed to ICSE when creating the client contains a BiodataInformationSource. Note that step 1 requires that where SV004 is called immediately after SV003, all identity information sent in the SV003 request must also be present in the SV004 request. The ESB takes the identities provided by the consumer in the SV004 request and compares them against the identities returned from the previous call to SV002. For each match found, the BiodataInformationSource against an identity provided by the consumer is added to the matched identity returned by SV002. For all identities returned from the previous call to SV002 which are not matched, the BiodataInformationSource is defaulted to 7. The following identity attributes must be the same in both the SV002 RetrievePartyResponse message and the SV004 ModifyPartyRequest message for an identity to be considered matched:
FamilyName
GivenName
BirthDate (BirthDateDay, BirthDateMonth, BirthDateYear)
SexType
BirthCountryCode
NameTitleText
NameUsage
Note: NameUsageStartDate is not included when matching since SV002 will not return this when the ICSE client does not exist.
ESB creates a ClientMaintenenceRequest message with the Party Id provided by the consumer and the party data returned in the SV002 RetrievePartyResponse message (including any updated name types as per step 5) and invokes the ICSE service
Since no CID was provided, ICSE performs a query to determine whether or not there is an ICSE client associated with the Party Id. If there is not an ICSE client associated with the Party Id, ICSE creates a new client with the party data provided. If there is an ICSE client associated with the Party Id, ICSE simply ignores the party data in the ClientMaintenanceRequest message. In either case, ICSE replies with the ClientMaintenanceRequest message with the CID that either already existed or has just been created.
ESB creates a new ClientMaintenenceRequest message with the data provided by the consumer, plus the CID (which was obtained in step 3 or in step 5) and invokes the ICSE service
Since a CID was provided, ICSE applies the provided data to the client record, adding new and changed entities as required. ICSE then replies to the ESB with the ClientMaintenanceRepsonse message
ESB returns ModifyPartyResponse to consumer with the Party Id, and includes the CID if a new client was created in ICSE

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. All expected and actual Movements associated to a party can be retrieved and filtered based on a date range and the movement type.
models.readme:
Service Usage

A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. All expected and actual Movements associated to a party can be retrieved and filtered based on a date range and the movement type.

Service Behaviour

This service retrieves all movements associated to a party including a collection of information that is stored in TRIPS defining the movement. A valid ID to uniquely identifier the party and optionally the date range and movement type is supplied.

The retrieved data consists of:

Expected Movements; Flight\Vessel Number, Expected travel dates, times, ports, directions etc

Actual Movements; Flight\Vessel Number, Expected travel dates, times, ports, directions etc

SV288 will be used to retrieve the required identifiers to pass to TRIPS. The unique ID for the party will be resolved to a PID and an SPL. If PID is supplied SV288 will still be invoked to retrieve the SPL.

If the End Date passed in is greater than 1989, historical movements file is not checked as all historical movements are pre 1989 only. This logic is handled by the TRIPS provider to save processing.

Service Variants

None.

Service Dependencies

None.

Service Composition

This service is a composite service i.e. it is composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

  1. An event is generated by the Service Consumer when they invoke the SearchMovement service on the ESB by sending a valid SearchMovementRequest.xml file to the ESB.
  2. ESB invokes RetrieveConsolidatedPartyIdentifiers (SV288) with the identifier provided by the consumer.
  3. ESB extracts the active PID and active SPL (where they exist) and populates these identifiers into the SearchMovementRequest.xml
  4. SearchMovementRequest.xml is then parsed and eSQL produces a flat file request to TRIPS.
  5. ESB invokes the provider TRIPS with this flat file.
  6. TRIPS responds with the flat file response. ESB processes this using eSQL and converts the flat file to a valid SearchMovementResponse.xml
  7. ESB adds any code reference lookups and code translations to the SearchMovementResponse.xml
  8. ESB returns SearchMovementResponse.xml to the consumer
    1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when SV288 raises an error.
  9. SV288 Returns an error code
  10. ESB will not call TRIPS
  11. ESB passes this error code on unchanged to the consumer.
    1.1.2 Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when SV288 returns no SPL or PID.
    SV288 returns a valid response but it contains no PID or SPL
    ESB will not call TRIPS
    ESB will pass back a warning and a valid empty SearchMovementResponse.xml

Service State Management Decisions

If either provider system returns an error code at any stage of the service execution, the message flow will be stopped and the error returned to the consumer. This service will not return partial response messages.

models.description:
Service Usage

The service will be used by CCMD&S, CCP, GVP, ECS and BSP to show the business dealings a party can have with DIAC. This service provides a consolidated summary of active and past business dealings for a nominated party. The information will be retrieved from the CDH.
models.readme:
Service Usage

The service will be used by CCMD&S, CCP, GVP, ECS and BSP to show the business dealings a party can have with DIAC. This service provides a consolidated summary of active and past business dealings for a nominated party. The information will be retrieved from the CDH.

Service Behaviour

A request is sent from the consumer to the CDH requesting a business summary for a party. CDH returns returns all information or the business dealings with no orchestration of calls to another provider.

The request will contain a System of Entry (SoE) code or party role identifier to identify the party concerned. Optionally, the service will allow one or more business dealing categories to enable CDH to return only specific business areas. If there is no specific business dealing category in the request then it is assumed that all business categories for that party will be retrieved.

When CDH returns the business summary in the service response format to the consumer. A party, with respect to this service, may be either a person or an organisation. This service will return all roles associated with the business dealing.

The service returns a list of associated business dealings, such as nominations and sponsorships, if such a relationship is stored in CDH. The only exception to this is when GVP create and master a business dealing and subsequently create a dummy, or skeleton, business dealing in ICSE. This is a situation where two identifiers for the one business dealing exist. To cater for this an AssociatedBusinessDealingMsg will be created to indicate the ICSE skeleton business dealing and the business dealing relationship will be 'ICSE skeleton'.

The number of results returned may be restricted by business dealing category or by a date range. A record start and end number may be sent to indicate only a subset of records be returned from a total set either for all business dealings or for specific business dealings. If specific pagination for a business dealing is specified then it must also be in the top element. A zero in either field indicates no upper or lower bound.

To ensure that pagination can happen, the order of the business dealing records is by last update date.

A flag may be sent to indicate no related party information is to be sent.

The response will also indicate, for each business dealing category, how many records have been returned from how many possible records.

Note: A role identifier will be returned in the response instead of one or more party identifiers if and only if a role identifier is sent in the request AND no party is found in CDH.

Service Variants

There are no service variants

Service Dependencies

This service is dependent on CDH having an appropriate API, or set of APIs, that return the business summary given a party id and, optionally, a business category.

Service Composition

This service is a single service calling CDH only. This service currently retrieves one, and only one, party back. Although the XSD for the request and response has been designed to allow many different parties to be requested for and returned, this alternative functionality is not implemented. IF identifiers for many different parties are sent in the request the service will return the details for one of them. Which party it would pick is not defined; but the service itself cannot tell that the parties are not multiple and therefore cannot return an error (unless it tries every party and rejects the duplicates).

Service Flow

  1. The consumer generates a RetrieveConsolidatedPartyBusinessSummary service call to CDH.

  2. Within the request structure there are a number of attributes designed to reduce the size of the return XML. These are:
    a. Filter (i.e. active or inactive business dealings). The values are ACTIVE, INACTIVE and ALL. Default is ACTIVE;
    b Subset. Values are 0 (all business dealings returned) or 1 (only the latest business dealing returned);
    c. StartDate/EndDate - Allows a date range;
    d. Offset Start/Offset Count - Allows a form of pagination over the set of data (assuming all business dealings are sorted from earliest to latest); and
    e. Related Party Flag - A boolean to indicate if related parties are returned

  3. It is recommended that the consumer provide their system of record ID, for example Siebel should supply a SCID

  4. The data is gathered from CDH and a RetrieveConsolidatedPartyBusinessSummaryResponse message is returned

ALTERNATE FLOW 1
If an error is detected then CDH will raise an Enterprise error message

ALTERNATE FLOW 2
If the party is not found then CDH will raise an Enterprise warning message

ALTERNATE FLOW 3
If the service call times out then a message will be returned to the consumer indicating this.

Transformation

See the micro documentation.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management is required.

Service Usage

A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. A Partys interaction with DIAC is defined by one or many different Roles e.g. a Person can have the role of Applicant, Sponsor or Agent. An Organisation can have roles including Agency and Sponsor.
models.readme:
Service Usage

A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. A Partys interaction with DIAC is defined by one or many different Roles e.g. a Person can have the role of Applicant, Sponsor or Agent. An Organisation can have roles including Agency and Sponsor.

This service retrieves Party Contact Method information relating to a specific Party application, along with other relevant data and related business context information from the ICSE provider system. Contact method information covers relevant postal address, phone, fax or email information relating to the application.

The contact methods will be limited to only those contacts where the Usage code is set to HOME, MOBILE, POSTAL and BUSINESS. It will therefore exclude codes such as OTHER-HOME, OTHER-BUSINESS etc

Note: This service will not retrieve Agent information from ICSE as currently done by Service SV002 - Retrieve Party.

Service Behaviour

This service retrieves a set of contact method information relating to a specific Party application, selected using a valid CDH Party Id, CID (ICSE Client Id - unique identifier of a client in ICSE). Although the service is considered to use ICSE as its sole provider, if a consumer identifies a party using a CDH Party Id, a call will be made to the CDH to resolve the identifier into a CID utilizable by the ICSE system.

The request information consists of:

Identifier; the specific identifier for the required Party
Identifier Type; the type of identifier used (limited to CID or CDH Party Id for the SfP7 release). Where CID is used no resolving of the ID is required and the service call will be more efficient.

The retrieved data consists of:

Contact method information; a collection of contact details relating to the specified Partys application, comprising of:
o Address
o Phone
o Fax
Email information

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer providing a valid unique CDH Party Id or ICSE CID (Client Identifier) for a Party.
If the consumer identifies a Party using a CDH Party Id, the ESB must use the SV176 Transform Identifier service to resolve the identifier into a CID, utilizable by the ICSE system.

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

  1. An event is generated by the Service Consumer when they invoke the RetrievePartyApplicationContactDetails service on the ESB by sending a valid RetrievePartyApplicaitonContactDetailsRequest.xml file to the ESB.
  2. ESB invokes the primary provider ICSE as follows:
    a. ESB will transform RetrievePartyApplicaitonContactDetailsRequest.xml to ICSE.ICSVCLNTRTRVSRVCRequest as per data mappings in the SV279v02.00.xls micro design spreadsheet.
    If the identifier used in the request is a CDH Party Id, at this point the ESB will utilize the SV176 Transform Identifier service to resolve the identifier to a CID. Flow will then continue as per normal. If any identifier type other than Party Id of CID is used, stop flow and return message to consumer (SV279.MSG-E10).
    b. ESB invokes the ICSE.RetrieveParty service
    c. ICSE excecutes the ICSE.RetrieveParty service and returns the ICSE.ICSVCLNTRTRVSRVCResponse file to the ESB. If the Party does not exist in ICSE then stop flow and return message to consumer (SV279.MSG-E11). d. ESB transforms ICSE.RetrievePartyResponse.xml into RetrievePartyApplicaitonContactDetailsResponse.xml as per data mappings in the SV279v02.00.xls micro design spreadsheet.
  3. ESB returns RetrievePartyApplicaitonContactDetailsResponse.xml to the consumer.
    1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
    The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
  4. Primary provider ICSE returns a specific error code to the ESB; see section 4 of this document for a full listing of Return Codes and Messages.
  5. ESB transforms error code into Enterprise Error Message.
  6. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload to the consumer.

1.1.2 Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the ESB raises an error before or while attempting to contact the primary provider, it will respond to the consumer with the relevant Enterprise Error payload. See section 4 of this document for a full listing of Return Codes and Messages.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.

models.description:
Service Usage

This service enables a consumer to retrieve information about a nominated Agent and any Agency(ies) that the nominated Agent is related to.
models.readme:
Service Usage

This service enables a consumer to retrieve information about a nominated Agent and any Agency(ies) that the nominated Agent is related to.
An Agent is a Party with the Role of Agent. A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. A Party has a Party Role that is a role independent of any specific DIAC business context. For example, DIAC may have an interest in an Agent that is independent of the agents involvement in any specific visa application. Within DIAC, the Party Role of Agent encompasses:
Unregistered Migration Agent
Registered Migration Agent
Travel Agent
Education Agent.
Agents may also be employed by an organisation referred to as an Agency. In these instances, it is possible for a relationship to exist between an Agent and one or more Agencies.

Service Behaviour

This service retrieves Agent information matching to the supplied Agent Id (Role Id) or Migration Agent Registration Authority (MARA) Registration ID or any other Party Identifier for example PID, SCID,, which must resolve to an Agent Id or Mara Id. ICSE is used as sole provider for Agent information returned by this service.
To invoke the service a consumer provides a pair of parameters as under:
Identifier
IdentifierType
Value supplied for IdentifierType (System) can be of one of the following types
MARAID ICSEAgentID CDHPARTYID CID HATSCLIENTID PID REVENUERECEIPTING_ID
SCID
SPL

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer providing a valid Identifier which resolves to an Agent Id or MARA ID in ICSE.

Service Composition

This service is a composite service. It calls SV288 Retrieve Consolidated Party Identifiers.

Service Flow

  1. An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Retrieve Agent Details service on the ESB by sending a SOAP XML message wrapping a message conforming to ESB.RetreiveAgentDetailsRequest.
  2. ESB checks IdentifierType. If IdentifierType is of type AGENTID or MARAID then flow proceeds to Step 3.
    a. Using SV288 resolve party Identifier to Identifier of type AGENTID or MARAID
    b. If Identifier does not get resolved to either type of AGENTID or MARAID then return SV287.MSG-E06
  3. ESB transforms the incoming request message to ICSE RetrieveAgentDetailRequest as per DIMA_DCD d15 Service Specification - SV287-v01.0 Retrieve Agent Details.xls and invokes ICSE.
  4. ICSE executes the retrieve agent process and returns an XML message with Agent Details as per ICSE.RetrieveAgentDetailsResponse to ESB.
    Note: ICSE will return details under agent_dtls only when the supplied id belongs to Migration Agent.
  5. ESB transforms the ICSE.RetrieveAgentDetailsResponse message to ESB.RetrieveAgentDetailsResponse and returns it to consumer.

1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.

  1. Primary provider ICSE returns a specific error code to the ESB
  2. ESB transforms error code into Enterprise Error Message.
  3. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload to the consumer.
    1.1.2 Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
    If the ESB raises an error before or while attempting to contact the primary provider, it will respond to the consumer with the relevant Enterprise Error payload.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
